#. type: Title ==
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "Storage and Partitioning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:277
msgid ""
"Commands in this section are used to determine your system's storage options "
"and partitioning."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:279
#, no-wrap
msgid "autopart (optional) - Automatic Partitioning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:282
msgid ""
"Automatically creates partitions: a root (`/`) partition (1 GB or larger), a "
"`swap` partition, and an appropriate `/boot` partition for the architecture. "
"On large enough drives (50{nbsp}GB and larger), this also creates a `/home` "
"partition."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:287
msgid ""
"The [command]#autopart# option cannot be used together with the "
"[command]#part/partition#, [command]#raid#, [command]#logvol#, or "
"[command]#volgroup# options in the same Kickstart file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--type=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:291
msgid ""
"Selects one of the predefined automatic partitioning schemes you want to "
"use. Accepts the following values:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:293
msgid "`lvm`: The LVM partitioning scheme."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:295
msgid "`btrfs`: The Btrfs partitioning scheme."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:297
msgid "`plain`: Regular partitions with no LVM or Btrfs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:299
msgid "`thinp`: The LVM Thin Provisioning partitioning scheme."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:301
msgid ""
"The created partitioning scheme will follow the recommended scheme described "
"at xref:install/Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-installation-gui-manual-"
"partitioning-recommended[Recommended Partitioning Scheme]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:302
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:738
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:976
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1047
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--fstype=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:303
msgid ""
"Specify a supported file system (such as `ext4` or `xfs`) to replace the "
"default when doing automatic partitioning."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:304
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nolvm#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:305
msgid ""
"Do not use LVM or Btrfs for automatic partitioning. This option is equal to "
"[option]#--type=plain#."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:306
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:777
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1000
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1064
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--encrypted#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:307
msgid ""
"Encrypts all partitions. This is equivalent to checking the `Encrypt "
"partitions` check box on the initial partitioning screen during a manual "
"graphical installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:308
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:779
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1002
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1066
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--passphrase=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:309
msgid "Provides a default system-wide passphrase for all encrypted devices."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:310
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:783
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1006
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1070
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--escrowcert=pass:attributes[{blank}]_URL_of_X.509_certificate_pass:attributes[{blank}]#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:311
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1007
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1071
msgid ""
"Stores data encryption keys of all encrypted volumes as files in `/root`, "
"encrypted using the X.509 certificate from the URL specified with "
"_URL_of_X.509_certificate_. The keys are stored as a separate file for each "
"encrypted volume. This option is only meaningful if [option]#--encrypted# is "
"specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:312
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:785
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1008
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1072
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--backuppassphrase#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:313
msgid ""
"Adds a randomly-generated passphrase to each encrypted volume. Store these "
"passphrases in separate files in `/root`, encrypted using the X.509 "
"certificate specified with [option]#--escrowcert#. This option is only "
"meaningful if [option]#--escrowcert# is specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:314
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:781
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1004
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1068
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--cipher=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:315
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:782
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1005
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1069
msgid ""
"Specifies which type of encryption will be used if the "
"[application]*Anaconda* default `aes-xts-plain64` is not satisfactory. You "
"must use this option together with the [option]#--encrypted# option; by "
"itself it has no effect. Available types of encryption are listed in the "
"[citetitle]_Fedora Security Guide_, available at link:++https://docs."
"fedoraproject.org/++[]. Using either `aes-xts-plain64` or `aes-cbc-essiv:"
"sha256` is strongly recommended."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:316
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:812
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1010
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1074
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--luks-version=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:317
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:813
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1011
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1075
msgid ""
"Specifies which version of LUKS should be used to encrypt the system. Only "
"relevant if [option]#--encrypted# is also specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:318
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:814
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1012
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1076
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--pbkdf=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:319
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:815
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1013
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1077
msgid ""
"Sets Password-Based Key Derivation Function (PBKDF) algorithm for the LUKS "
"keyslot. Only relevant if [option]#--encrypted# is also specified. See the "
"`cryptsetup(8)` man page for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:320
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:816
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1014
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1078
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#pbkdf-memory=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:321
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:817
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1015
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1079
msgid ""
"Sets the memory cost for PBKDF. Only relevant if [option]#--encrypted# is "
"also specified. See the `cryptsetup(8)` man page for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:322
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:818
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1016
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1080
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#pbkdf-time=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:323
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:819
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1017
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1081
msgid ""
"Sets the number of miliseconds to spend with PBKDF passphrase processing. "
"Only relevant if [option]#--encrypted# is also specified. See information "
"about the [option]#--iter-time# option in the `cryptsetup(8)` man page for "
"more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:325
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:329
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:821
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:825
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1019
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1023
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1083
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1087
msgid ""
"Only one of [option]#--pbkdf-time=# or [option]#--pbkdf-iterations=# can be "
"specified at the same time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:326
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:822
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1020
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1084
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#pbkdf-iterations=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:327
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:823
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1021
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1085
msgid ""
"Sets the number of iterations for passphrase processing directly, and avoids "
"PBKDF benchmark. Only relevant if [option]#--encrypted# is also specified. "
"See information about the [option]#--pbkdf-force-iterations# option in the "
"`cryptsetup(8)` man page for more information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "bootloader (required) - Configure Boot Loader"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:334
msgid "Specifies how the boot loader should be installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:339
msgid ""
"You should always use a password to protect your boot loader. An unprotected "
"boot loader can allow a potential attacker to modify the system's boot "
"options and gain unauthorized access to the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:346
msgid ""
"Some systems require a special partition for installing the boot loader. The "
"type and size of this partition depends on whether the disk you are "
"installing the boot loader to uses the _Master Boot Record_ (MBR) or a _GUID "
"Partition Table_ (GPT) schema. For more information, see xref:install/"
"Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-installation-gui-storage-partitioning-"
"bootloader[Boot Loader Installation]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:349
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--append=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:350
msgid ""
"Specifies additional kernel parameters. To specify multiple parameters, "
"separate them with spaces. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:354
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#bootloader --location=mbr --append=\"hdd=ide-scsi ide=nodma\"#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:357
msgid ""
"The [option]#rhgb# and [option]#quiet# parameters are always used, even if "
"you do not specify them here or do not use the [option]#--append=# command "
"at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:358
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--boot-drive=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:359
msgid ""
"Specifies which drive the boot loader should be written to, and therefore "
"which drive the computer will boot from. If you use a multipath device as "
"the boot drive, specify only one member of the device."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:364
msgid ""
"The [option]#--boot-drive=# option is currently being ignored in {PRODUCT} "
"installations on IBM System{nbsp}z systems using the [application]*zipl* "
"boot loader. When [application]*zipl* is installed, it determines the boot "
"drive on its own."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:368
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Not* specifying this option will result in the following behavior:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:370
msgid ""
"If the [option]#--driveorder=# option was used, [application]*Anaconda* will "
"install the boot loader on the first valid device specified in the drive "
"order."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:372
msgid ""
"The first present and valid disk containing a `/boot` partition will be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:374
msgid ""
"If none of the above applies, then the first valid storage device from the "
"list of all detected devices will be used to install the boot loader."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:375
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--leavebootorder#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:376
msgid ""
"Prevents the installation program from making changes to the existing list "
"of bootable images on UEFI or ISeries/PSeries systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:377
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--driveorder=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:378
msgid "Specifies which drive is first in the BIOS boot order. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:382
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#bootloader --driveorder=sda,hda#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:384
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--location=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:385
msgid ""
"Specifies where the boot record is written. Valid values are the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:387
msgid ""
"`mbr` - The default option. Depends on whether the drive uses the Master "
"Boot Record (MBR) or GUID Partition Table (GPT) scheme:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:389
msgid ""
"On a GPT-formatted disk, this option will install stage 1.5 of the boot "
"loader into the BIOS boot partition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:391
msgid ""
"On an MBR-formatted disk, stage 1.5 will be installed into the empty space "
"between the MBR and the first partition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:393
msgid ""
"`partition` - Install the boot loader on the first sector of the partition "
"containing the kernel."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:395
msgid "`none` - Do not install the boot loader."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:397
msgid "In most cases, this option does not need to be specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:398
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:671
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1769
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1936
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--password=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:399
msgid ""
"If using [application]*GRUB2* as the boot loader, sets the boot loader "
"password to the one specified with this option. This should be used to "
"restrict access to the [application]*GRUB2* shell, where arbitrary kernel "
"options can be passed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:401
msgid ""
"If a password is specified, [application]*GRUB2* will also ask for a user "
"name. The user name is always `root`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:402
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1707
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1771
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1890
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--iscrypted#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:403
msgid ""
"Normally, when you specify a boot loader password using the [option]#--"
"password=# option, it will be stored in the Kickstart file in plain text. If "
"you want to encrypt the password, use this option and an encrypted password."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:405
msgid ""
"To generate an encrypted password, use the [command]#grub2-mkpasswd-pbkdf2# "
"command, enter the password you want to use, and copy the command's output "
"(the hash starting with `grub.pbkdf2`) into the Kickstart file. An example "
"[command]#bootloader# Kickstart entry with an encrypted password will look "
"similar to the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:410
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#bootloader --iscrypted --password=grub.pbkdf2.sha512.10000.5520C6C9832F3AC3D149AC0B24BE69E2D4FB0DBEEDBD29CA1D30A044DE2645C4C7A291E585D4DC43F8A4D82479F8B95CA4BA4381F8550510B75E8E0BB2938990.C688B6F0EF935701FF9BD1A8EC7FE5BD2333799C98F28420C5CC8F1A2A233DE22C83705BB614EA17F3FDFDF4AC2161CEA3384E56EB38A2E39102F5334C47405E#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:413
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--timeout=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:414
msgid ""
"Specifies the amount of time the boot loader will wait before booting the "
"default option (in seconds)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:415
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--default=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:416
msgid "Sets the default boot image in the boot loader configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:417
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--extlinux#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:418
msgid ""
"Use the [application]*extlinux* boot loader instead of [application]*GRUB2*. "
"This option only works on systems supported by [application]*extlinux*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:419
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1734
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--disabled#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:420
msgid ""
"Do not attempt to install a boot loader. This option overrides all other "
"boot loader configuration; all other boot loader options will be ignored and "
"no boot loader packages will be installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:421
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nombr#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:422
msgid ""
"Install the boot loader configuration and support files, but do not modify "
"the MBR."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:424
#, no-wrap
msgid "btrfs (optional) - Create Btrfs Volume or Subvolume"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:427
msgid "Create a Btrfs volume or subvolume. For a volume, the syntax is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:432
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#btrfs _mntpoint_ --data=pass:attributes[{blank}]_level_ --metadata=pass:attributes[{blank}]_level_ [--label=] _partitions_pass:attributes[{blank}]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:436
msgid ""
"One or more partitions can be specified in _partitions_. When specifying "
"more than one partitions, the entries must be separated by a single space. "
"See xref:exam-kickstart-create-btrfs[Creating Btrfs Volumes and Subvolumes] "
"for a demonstration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:438
msgid "For a subvolume, the syntax is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:443
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#btrfs _mntpoint_ --subvol --name=pass:attributes[{blank}]_name_ _parent_pass:attributes[{blank}]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:447
msgid ""
"_parent_ should be the identifier of the subvolume's parent volume, _name_ "
"with a name for the subvolume, and _mntpoint_ is the location where the file "
"system is mounted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:448
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--data=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:449
msgid ""
"RAID level to use for file system *data* (such as `0`, `1`, or `10`). This "
"parameter is optional, has no meaning for subvolumes, and requires more than "
"one physical disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:450
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--metadata=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:451
msgid ""
"RAID level to use for file system/volume *metadata* (such as `0`, `1`, or "
"`10`). This parameter is optional, has no meaning for subvolumes, and "
"requires more than one physical disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:452
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:749
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:987
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1058
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--label=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:453
msgid ""
"Specify a label for the Btrfs file system. If the given label is already in "
"use by another file system, a new label will be created. This option has no "
"meaning for subvolumes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:454
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--subvol#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:455
msgid "Create a Btrfs subvolume instead of a volume."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:457
msgid "Set a name for a Btrfs subvolume."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:458
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--noformat# or [option]#--useexisting#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:459
msgid ""
"Use an existing Btrfs volume (or subvolume) and do not reformat the file "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:460
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:747
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:985
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1056
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--mkfsoptions=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:461
msgid ""
"Specifies additional parameters to be passed to the program that makes a "
"filesystem on this volume or subvolume. No processing is done on the list of "
"arguments, so they must be supplied in a format that can be passed directly "
"to the mkfs program. This means multiple options should be comma-separated "
"or surrounded by double quotes, depending on the filesystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:463
msgid ""
"The following example shows how to create a Btrfs volume from member "
"partitions on three disks with subvolumes for `/` and `/home`. The main "
"volume is not mounted or used directly in this example."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:465
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating Btrfs Volumes and Subvolumes"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:474
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#part btrfs.01 --size=6000 --ondisk=sda#\n"
"[command]#part btrfs.02 --size=6000 --ondisk=sdb#\n"
"[command]#part btrfs.03 --size=6000 --ondisk=sdc#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:478
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#btrfs none --data=0 --metadata=1 --label=f{PRODVER} btrfs.01 btrfs.02 btrfs.03#\n"
"[command]#btrfs / --subvol --name=root LABEL=f{PRODVER}#\n"
"[command]#btrfs /home --subvol --name=home f{PRODVER}#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "clearpart (optional) - Remove All Existing Partitions"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:487
msgid ""
"Removes partitions from the system, prior to creation of new partitions. By "
"default, no partitions are removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:492
msgid ""
"If the [command]#clearpart# command is used, then the [command]#part --"
"onpart# command cannot be used on a logical partition."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:496
msgid ""
"For a detailed example of partitioning including the [command]#clearpart# "
"command, see xref:sect-kickstart-example-advanced-partitioning[Advanced "
"Partitioning Example]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:497
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--all#"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:498
msgid "Erases all partitions from the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:503
msgid ""
"This option will erase all disks which can be reached by the installer, "
"including any attached network storage. Use this option with caution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:506
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:588
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--drives=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:507
msgid ""
"Specifies which drives to clear partitions from. For example, the following "
"clears all the partitions on the first two drives on the primary IDE "
"controller:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:511
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#clearpart --drives=hda,hdb --all#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:514
msgid ""
"To clear a multipath device, use the format `disk/by-id/scsi-_WWID_pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]`, where _WWID_ is the _world-wide identifier_ for the "
"device. For example, to clear a disk with WWID "
"`58095BEC5510947BE8C0360F604351918`, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:518
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#clearpart --drives=disk/by-id/scsi-58095BEC5510947BE8C0360F604351918#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:521
msgid ""
"This format is preferable for all multipath devices, but if errors arise, "
"multipath devices that do not use _logical volume management_ (LVM) can also "
"be cleared using the format `disk/by-id/dm-uuid-mpath-_WWID_pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]`, where _WWID_ is the _world-wide identifier_ for the "
"device. For example, to clear a disk with WWID "
"`2416CD96995134CA5D787F00A5AA11017`, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:525
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#clearpart --drives=disk/by-id/dm-uuid-mpath-2416CD96995134CA5D787F00A5AA11017#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:531
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:613
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:961
msgid ""
"Never specify multipath devices by device names like `mpatha`. Device names "
"such as this are not specific to a particular disk. The disk named `/dev/"
"mpatha` during installation might not be the one that you expect it to be. "
"Therefore, the [command]#clearpart# command could target the wrong disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:535
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:617
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:965
msgid ""
"Starting with Fedora 25, you can combine multiple ways of specifying storage "
"targets in one command, using the pipe (\"pass:attributes[{blank}]`|`pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]\") as a delimiter. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:538
#, no-wrap
msgid "clearpart --drives=sd*|hd*|vda,/dev/vdc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:541
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:623
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:971
msgid ""
"The above will match either of `sd*`, `hd*`, *or* `vda` *and* `/dev/vdc`. "
"Variants are processed from left to right, and at least one of them must "
"match for the command to succeed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:542
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--list=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:543
msgid ""
"Specifies which partitions to clear. This option overrides the [option]#--"
"all# and [option]#--linux# options if used. Can be used across different "
"drives. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:547
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#clearpart --list=sda2,sda3,sdb1#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:549
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--disklabel=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:550
msgid "Create a set disk label when relabeling a disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:551
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--linux#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:552
msgid "Erases all Linux partitions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:553
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--none#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:554
msgid ""
"Do not remove any partitions. This is the default behavior - using this "
"option is the same as not using the [command]#clearpart# command at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:559
msgid ""
"Using the [command]#clearpart --all# command in a Kickstart file to remove "
"all existing partitions during the installation will cause "
"[application]*Anaconda* to pause and prompt you for a confirmation. If you "
"need to perform the installation automatically with no interaction, add the "
"[command]#zerombr# command to your Kickstart file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:563
#, no-wrap
msgid "fcoe (optional) - Configure Fibre Channel Over Ethernet Devices"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:566
msgid ""
"Specify which FCoE devices should be activated automatically in addition to "
"those discovered by _Enhanced Disk Drive Services_ (EDD)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:570
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#fcoe --nic=pass:attributes[{blank}]_name_ [--dcp= | --autovlan]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:572
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nic=# (required)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:573
msgid "Name of the device to be activated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:574
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--dcb=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:575
msgid "Establish _Data Center Bridging_ (DCB) settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:576
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--autovlan#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:577
msgid "Discover VLANs automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:579
#, no-wrap
msgid "ignoredisk (optional) - Ignore Specified Disks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:582
msgid ""
"Causes the installation program to ignore the specified disks. This is "
"useful if you use autopartition and want to be sure that some disks are "
"ignored. For example, without [command]#ignoredisk#, attempting to deploy on "
"a SAN cluster the Kickstart would fail, as the installation program detects "
"passive paths to the SAN that return no partition table."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:586
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#ignoredisk --drives= | --only-use= [--interactive]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:589
msgid ""
"Specify one or more drives to ignore. Multiple drives can be specified as a "
"comma-separated list. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:593
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#ignoredisk --drives=sda,sdc#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:596
msgid ""
"To ignore a multipath device that does not use _logical volume management_ "
"(LVM), use the format `disk/by-id/dm-uuid-mpath-_WWID_pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]`, where _WWID_ is the _world-wide identifier_ for the "
"device. For example, to ignore a disk with WWID "
"`2416CD96995134CA5D787F00A5AA11017`, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:600
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#ignoredisk --drives=disk/by-id/dm-uuid-mpath-2416CD96995134CA5D787F00A5AA11017#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:603
msgid ""
"Multipath devices that use LVM are not assembled until after "
"[application]*Anaconda* has parsed the Kickstart file. Therefore, you cannot "
"specify these devices in the format `dm-uuid-mpath`. Instead, to ignore a "
"multipath device that uses LVM, use the format `disk/by-id/scsi-_WWID_pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]`, where _WWID_ is the _world-wide identifier_ for the "
"device. For example, to ignore a disk with WWID "
"`58095BEC5510947BE8C0360F604351918`, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:607
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#ignoredisk --drives=disk/by-id/scsi-58095BEC5510947BE8C0360F604351918#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:620
#, no-wrap
msgid "ignoredisk --drives=sd*|hd*|vda,/dev/vdc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:624
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--only-use=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:625
msgid ""
"Specifies a list of disks for the installation program to use. All other "
"disks are ignored. For example, to use disk `sda` during installation and "
"ignore all other disks:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:629
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#ignoredisk --only-use=sda#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:632
msgid "To include a multipath device that does not use LVM:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:636
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#ignoredisk --only-use=disk/by-id/dm-uuid-mpath-2416CD96995134CA5D787F00A5AA11017#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:639
msgid "To include a multipath device that uses LVM:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:643
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#ignoredisk --only-use=disk/by-id/scsi-58095BEC5510947BE8C0360F604351918#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:645
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--interactive#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:646
msgid "Allows you to manually navigate the advanced storage screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:648
#, no-wrap
msgid "iscsi (optional) - Configure iSCSI Devices"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:651
msgid ""
"Specifies additional iSCSI storage to be attached during installation. If "
"you use the [command]#iscsi# command, you must also assign a name to the "
"iSCSI node, using the [command]#iscsiname# command (see xref:sect-kickstart-"
"commands-iscsiname[iscsiname (optional) - Assign Name to iSCSI Device]. The "
"[command]#iscsiname# command must appear before the [command]#iscsi# command "
"in the Kickstart file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:653
msgid ""
"You should configure iSCSI storage in the system BIOS or firmware (iBFT for "
"Intel systems) rather than use the [command]#iscsi# command if possible. If "
"you do so, [application]*Anaconda* automatically detects and uses disks "
"configured in BIOS or firmware and no special configuration is necessary in "
"the Kickstart file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:655
msgid ""
"If you must use the [command]#iscsi# command, make sure that networking is "
"activated at the beginning of the installation, and that the "
"[command]#iscsi# command appears in the Kickstart file *before* you refer to "
"iSCSI disks with commands such as [command]#clearpart# or "
"[command]#ignoredisk#."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:659
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#iscsi --ipaddr=  --port=  [--target= | --iface= | --user= | --password= | --reverse-user= | --reverse-password=]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:661
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ipaddr=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:662
msgid "The IP address of the target to connect to."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:663
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1253
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1843
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1934
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--port=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:664
msgid "The port number (typically `3260`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:665
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--target=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:666
msgid "Target _IQN_ (iSCSI Qualified Name)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:667
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--iface=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:668
msgid ""
"Bind the connection to a specific network interface instead of using the "
"default one determined by the network layer. Once used, it must be specified "
"in all instances of the [command]#iscsi# command in the entire Kickstart "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:669
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--user=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:670
msgid "User name required to authenticate with the target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:672
msgid "Password that corresponds with the user name specified for the target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:673
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--reverse-user=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:674
msgid ""
"User name required to authenticate with the initiator from a target using "
"reverse CHAP authentication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:675
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--reverse-password=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:676
msgid ""
"Password that corresponds with the user name specified for the initiator."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:678
#, no-wrap
msgid "iscsiname (optional) - Assign Name to iSCSI Device"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:681
msgid ""
"Assigns a name to an iSCSI node specified by the [command]#iscsi# command "
"(xref:sect-kickstart-commands-iscsi[iscsi (optional) - Configure iSCSI "
"Devices]). This command is mandatory if you use the [command]#iscsi# "
"command, and it must be specified *before* you use [command]#iscsi#."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:685
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#iscsiname _iqn_pass:attributes[{blank}]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:688
#, no-wrap
msgid "logvol (optional) - Create LVM Logical Volume"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:691
msgid ""
"Create a logical volume for Logical Volume Management (LVM) with the syntax:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:695
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#logvol _mntpoint_ --vgname=  --name= [pass:attributes[{blank}]_options_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:701
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1148
msgid ""
"Do not use the dash (`-`) character in logical volume and volume group names "
"when installing {PRODUCT} using Kickstart. If this character is used, the "
"installation will finish normally, but the `/dev/mapper/` directory will "
"list these volumes and volume groups with every dash doubled. For example, a "
"volume group named `volgrp-01` containing a logical volume named `logvol-01` "
"will be listed as `/dev/mapper/volgrp--01-logvol--01`."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:703
msgid ""
"This limitation only applies to newly created logical volume and volume "
"group names. If you are reusing existing ones using the [option]#--noformat# "
"or [option]#--useexisting# option, their names will not be changed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:707
msgid ""
"For a detailed example of [command]#logvol# in action, see xref:sect-"
"kickstart-example-advanced-partitioning[Advanced Partitioning Example]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:708
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:865
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1037
#, no-wrap
msgid "_mntpoint_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:709
msgid ""
"Replace with the volume's mount point. This name can take the following "
"forms:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:710
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:867
#, no-wrap
msgid "`/pass:attributes[{blank}]_path_pass:attributes[{blank}]`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:711
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:868
msgid "A path to the mount point - for example, `/` or `/home`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:712
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:869
#, no-wrap
msgid "`swap`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:713
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:870
msgid "The partition is used as swap space."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:715
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:872
msgid ""
"To determine the size of the swap partition automatically, use the "
"[option]#--recommended# option:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:719
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:876
#, no-wrap
msgid "`swap --recommended`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:722
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:881
msgid ""
"To determine the size of the swap partition automatically but also allow "
"extra space for your system to hibernate, use the [option]#--hibernation# "
"option:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:726
#, no-wrap
msgid "`swap --hibernation`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:729
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:888
msgid ""
"The size assigned will be equivalent to the swap space assigned by "
"[option]#--recommended# plus the amount of RAM on your system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:731
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:890
msgid ""
"For the swap sizes assigned by these commands, see the section describing "
"swap in xref:install/Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-installation-gui-"
"manual-partitioning-recommended[Recommended Partitioning Scheme]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:732
#, no-wrap
msgid "`none`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:733
msgid "Used only when creating a thin pool volume."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:734
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:921
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1060
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1155
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--noformat#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:735
msgid "Use an existing logical volume and do not format it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:736
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1062
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1157
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--useexisting#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:737
msgid "Use an existing logical volume and format it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:739
msgid ""
"Sets the file system type for the logical volume. Valid values are `xfs`, "
"`ext2`, `ext3`, `ext4`, `swap`, and `vfat`. See xref:install/"
"Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-installation-gui-manual-partitioning-"
"filesystems[Device, File System and RAID Types] for information about "
"available file systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:740
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:978
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1049
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--fsoptions=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:741
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:979
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1050
msgid ""
"Specifies a free form string of options to be used when mounting the "
"filesystem. This string will be copied into the `/etc/fstab` file of the "
"installed system and should be enclosed in quotes. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:745
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:983
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1054
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--fsoptions=\"ro, x-systemd.device-timeout=0\"#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:748
msgid ""
"Specifies additional parameters to be passed to the program that makes a "
"filesystem on this logical volume. No processing is done on the list of "
"arguments, so they must be supplied in a format that can be passed directly "
"to the mkfs program. This means multiple options should be comma-separated "
"or surrounded by double quotes, depending on the filesystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:750
msgid "Sets a label for the logical volume."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:751
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:912
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--grow#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:752
msgid ""
"Grow the volume to fill available space (if any), or up to the limit set by "
"the [option]#--maxsize=# option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:753
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:899
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--size=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:754
msgid ""
"The size of the logical volume in megabytes. This option can not be used "
"together with the [option]#--percent=# option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:755
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--percent=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:756
msgid ""
"Specify the amount by which to grow the logical volume, as a percentage of "
"the free space in the volume group after any statically-sized logical "
"volumes are taken into account. This option can not be used together with "
"the [option]#--size=# and [option]#--grow# options."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:761
msgid ""
"When creating a new logical volume, you must either specify its size "
"statically using the [option]#--size=# option, or as a percentage of "
"remaining free space using the [option]#--percent=# option. You can not use "
"both of these options on the same logical volume."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:764
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:908
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--maxsize=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:765
msgid ""
"The maximum size in megabytes when the logical volume is set to grow. "
"Specify an integer value here such as `500` (do not include the unit)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:766
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:989
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--recommended#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:767
msgid ""
"Use this option when creating a `swap` logical volume to determine the size "
"of this volume automatically, based on your system's hardware. For details "
"about the recommended scheme, see xref:install/Installing_Using_Anaconda."
"adoc#sect-installation-gui-manual-partitioning-recommended[Recommended "
"Partitioning Scheme]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:772
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:995
msgid ""
"This option can only be used for partitions which result in a file system "
"such as the `/boot` partition and `swap` space. It can not be used to create "
"partitionsm, LVM physical or logical volumes or RAID members."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:775
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:910
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--resize#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:776
msgid ""
"Resize an existing logical volume. If you use this option, you must also "
"specify [option]#--useexisting# and [option]#--size#."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:778
msgid ""
"Specifies that this logical volume should be encrypted, using the passphrase "
"provided in the [option]#--passphrase=# option. If you do not specify a "
"passphrase, the installation program will use the default, system-wide "
"passphrase set with the [command]#autopart --passphrase# command, or stop "
"the installation and prompt you to provide a passphrase if no default is set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:780
msgid ""
"Specifies the passphrase to use when encrypting this logical volume. You "
"must use this option together with the [option]#--encrypted# option. This "
"option has no effect by itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:784
msgid ""
"Store data encryption keys of all encrypted volumes as files in `/root`, "
"encrypted using the X.509 certificate from the URL specified with "
"_URL_of_X.509_certificate_. The keys are stored as a separate file for each "
"encrypted volume. This option is only meaningful if [option]#--encrypted# is "
"specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:786
msgid ""
"Add a randomly-generated passphrase to each encrypted volume. Store these "
"passphrases in separate files in `/root`, encrypted using the X.509 "
"certificate specified with [option]#--escrowcert#. This option is only "
"meaningful if [option]#--escrowcert# is specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:787
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--thinpool#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:788
msgid "Creates a thin pool logical volume. (Use a mount point of `none`)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:789
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--metadatasize=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:790
msgid "Metadata area size (in MiB) for a new thin pool device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:791
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--chunksize=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:792
msgid "Chunk size (in KiB) for a new thin pool device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:793
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--thin#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:794
msgid "Create a thin logical volume. (Requires use of [option]#--poolname#)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:795
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--poolname=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:796
msgid ""
"Specify the name of the thin pool in which to create a thin logical volume. "
"Requires the [option]#--thin# option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:797
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--profile=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:798
msgid ""
"Specify the configuration profile name to use with thin logical volumes. If "
"used, the name will also be included in the metadata for the given logical "
"volume. By default, the available profiles are `default` and `thin-"
"performance` and are defined in the `/etc/lvm/profile` directory. See the "
"`lvm(8)` man page for additional information."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:799
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--cachepvs=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:800
msgid ""
"A comma-separated list of (fast) physical volumes which should be used for "
"LVM cache."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:801
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--cachesize=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:802
msgid ""
"Requested size of cache attached to the logical volume, in MiB. (Requires "
"the [option]#--cachepvs=# option.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:803
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--cachemode=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:804
msgid "Mode to be used for LVM cache (either `writeback` or `writethrough`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:809
msgid ""
"The [option]#--cachepvs=#, [option]#--cachesize=#, and [option]#--"
"cachemode=# options listed above are used to configure LVM caching. For more "
"information, see the `lvmcache(7)` man page."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:827
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1166
msgid ""
"Create one or more partitions first using xref:sect-kickstart-commands-"
"part[part (required) - Create Physical Partition], create the logical volume "
"group (xref:sect-kickstart-commands-volgroup[volgroup (optional) - Create "
"LVM Volume Group]), and then create logical volumes. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:834
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1173
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#part pv.01 --size 3000#\n"
"[command]#volgroup myvg pv.01#\n"
"[command]#logvol / --vgname=myvg --size=2000 --name=rootvol#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:838
#, no-wrap
msgid "part (required) - Create Physical Partition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:841
msgid "Creates a partition on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:843
msgid ""
"For a detailed example of [command]#part# in action, see xref:sect-kickstart-"
"example-advanced-partitioning[Advanced Partitioning Example]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:848
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#part|partition _mntpoint_ --name=pass:attributes[{blank}]_name_ --device=pass:attributes[{blank}]_device_ --rule=pass:attributes[{blank}]_rule_ [pass:attributes[{blank}]_options_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:855
msgid ""
"All partitions created are formatted as part of the installation process "
"unless [option]#--noformat# and [option]#--onpart=# are used."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:862
msgid ""
"If partitioning fails for any reason, diagnostic messages appear on virtual "
"console 3."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:866
msgid ""
"Where the partition is mounted. The value must be of one of the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:879
msgid ""
"The size assigned will be effective but not precisely calibrated for your "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:885
#, no-wrap
msgid "`swap--hibernation`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:891
#, no-wrap
msgid "`raid._id_pass:attributes[{blank}]`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:892
msgid "The partition is used for software RAID (see [command]#raid#)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:893
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pv._id_pass:attributes[{blank}]`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:894
msgid ""
"The partition is used for LVM (see xref:sect-kickstart-commands-part[part "
"(required) - Create Physical Partition])."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:895
#, no-wrap
msgid "`biosboot`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:896
msgid ""
"The partition will be used for a BIOS Boot partition. A 1 MB BIOS boot "
"partition is necessary on BIOS-based systems using a _GUID Partition Table_ "
"(GPT); the boot loader will be installed into it. It is not necessary on "
"UEFI systems. Also see xref:sect-kickstart-commands-part[part (required) - "
"Create Physical Partition]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:897
#, no-wrap
msgid "`/boot/efi`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:898
msgid ""
"An EFI System Partition. An EFI partition at least 50 MB in size is "
"necessary on UEFI-based systems; the recommended size is 200 MB. It is not "
"necessary on BIOS systems. Also see xref:sect-kickstart-commands-part[part "
"(required) - Create Physical Partition]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:900
msgid ""
"The minimum partition size in megabytes. Specify an integer value here such "
"as `500` (do not include the unit)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:905
msgid ""
"If the [option]#--size# value is too small, the installation will fail. Set "
"the [option]#--size# value as the minimum amount of space you require. For "
"size recommendations, see xref:install/Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-"
"installation-gui-manual-partitioning-recommended[Recommended Partitioning "
"Scheme]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:909
msgid ""
"The maximum partition size in megabytes when the partition is set to grow. "
"Specify an integer value here such as `500` (do not include the unit)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:911
msgid ""
"Resize an existing partition. When using this option, specify the new size "
"(in megabytes) using the [option]#--size=# option and the target partition "
"using the [option]#--onpart=# option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:913
msgid ""
"Tells the partition to grow to fill available space (if any), or up to the "
"maximum size setting."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:918
msgid ""
"If you use [option]#--grow=# without setting [option]#--maxsize=# on a swap "
"partition, [application]*Anaconda* will limit the maximum size of the swap "
"partition. For systems that have less than 2{nbsp}GB of physical memory, the "
"imposed limit is twice the amount of physical memory. For systems with more "
"than 2{nbsp}GB, the imposed limit is the size of physical memory plus 2{nbsp}"
"GB."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:922
msgid ""
"Specifies that the partition should not be formatted, for use with the "
"[option]#--onpart# command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:923
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--onpart=# or [option]#--usepart=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:924
msgid "Specifies the device on which to place the partition. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:928
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#partition /home --onpart=hda1#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:931
msgid "The above puts `/home` on `/dev/hda1`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:933
msgid ""
"These options can also add a partition to a logical volume. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:937
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#partition pv.1 --onpart=hda2#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:940
msgid ""
"The device must already exist on the system; the [option]#--onpart# option "
"will not create it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:941
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ondisk=# or [option]#--ondrive=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:942
msgid ""
"Forces the partition to be created on a particular disk. For example, "
"[option]#--ondisk=sdb# puts the partition on the second SCSI disk on the "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:944
msgid ""
"To specify a multipath device that does not use _logical volume management_ "
"(LVM), use the format `disk/by-id/dm-uuid-mpath-_WWID_pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]`, where _WWID_ is the _world-wide identifier_ for the "
"device. For example, to specify a disk with WWID "
"`2416CD96995134CA5D787F00A5AA11017`, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:948
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#part / --fstype=xfs --grow --asprimary --size=8192 --ondisk=disk/by-id/dm-uuid-mpath-2416CD96995134CA5D787F00A5AA11017#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:951
msgid ""
"Multipath devices that use LVM are not assembled until after "
"[application]*Anaconda* has parsed the Kickstart file. Therefore, you cannot "
"specify these devices in the format `dm-uuid-mpath`. Instead, to specify a "
"multipath device that uses LVM, use the format `disk/by-id/scsi-_WWID_pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]`, where _WWID_ is the _world-wide identifier_ for the "
"device. For example, to specify a disk with WWID "
"`58095BEC5510947BE8C0360F604351918`, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:955
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#part / --fstype=xfs --grow --asprimary --size=8192 --ondisk=disk/by-id/scsi-58095BEC5510947BE8C0360F604351918#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:968
#, no-wrap
msgid "part --onpart=sd*|hd*|vda,/dev/vdc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:972
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--asprimary#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:973
msgid ""
"Forces the partition to be allocated as a *primary* partition. If the "
"partition cannot be allocated as primary (usually due to too many primary "
"partitions being already allocated), the partitioning process will fail. "
"This option only makes sense when the disk uses a Master Boot Record (MBR); "
"for GUID Partition Table (GPT)-labeled disks this option has no meaning. For "
"information about primary (and extended) partitions, see xref:install/"
"Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-installation-gui-manual-partitioning-"
"recommended[Recommended Partitioning Scheme]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:974
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1045
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--fsprofile=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:975
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1046
msgid ""
"Specifies a _usage type_ to be passed to the program that makes a filesystem "
"on this partition. A usage type defines a variety of tuning parameters to be "
"used when making a filesystem. For this option to work, the filesystem must "
"support the concept of usage types and there must be a configuration file "
"that lists valid types. For `ext2`, `ext3`, `ext4`, this configuration file "
"is `/etc/mke2fs.conf`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:977
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1048
msgid ""
"Sets the file system type for the partition. Valid values are `xfs`, `ext2`, "
"`ext3`, `ext4`, `swap`, `vfat`, `efi` and `biosboot`. For information about "
"supported file systems, see xref:install/Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-"
"installation-gui-manual-partitioning-filesystems[Device, File System and "
"RAID Types]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:986
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1057
msgid ""
"Specifies additional parameters to be passed to the program that makes a "
"filesystem on this partition. No processing is done on the list of "
"arguments, so they must be supplied in a format that can be passed directly "
"to the mkfs program. This means multiple options should be comma-separated "
"or surrounded by double quotes, depending on the filesystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:988
msgid "Assign a label to an individual partition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:990
msgid ""
"Determine the size of the partition automatically. For details about the "
"recommended scheme, see xref:install/Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-"
"installation-gui-manual-partitioning-recommended[Recommended Partitioning "
"Scheme]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:998
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--onbiosdisk#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:999
msgid ""
"Forces the partition to be created on a particular disk as discovered by the "
"BIOS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1001
msgid ""
"Specifies that this partition should be encrypted, using the passphrase "
"provided in the [option]#--passphrase# option. If you do not specify a "
"passphrase, [application]*Anaconda* uses the default, system-wide passphrase "
"set with the [command]#autopart --passphrase# command, or stops the "
"installation and prompts you to provide a passphrase if no default is set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1003
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1067
msgid ""
"Specifies the passphrase to use when encrypting this partition. You must use "
"this option together with the [option]#--encrypted# option; by itself it has "
"no effect."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1009
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1073
msgid ""
"Add a randomly-generated passphrase to each encrypted partition. Store these "
"passphrases in separate files in `/root`, encrypted using the X.509 "
"certificate specified with [option]#--escrowcert#. This option is only "
"meaningful if [option]#--escrowcert# is specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1025
#, no-wrap
msgid "raid (optional) - Create Software RAID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1028
msgid "Assembles a software RAID device. This command is of the form:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1032
#, no-wrap
msgid "raid mntpoint --level=level --device=mddevice partitions*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1036
msgid ""
"For a detailed example of [command]#raid# in action, see xref:sect-kickstart-"
"example-advanced-partitioning[Advanced Partitioning Example]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1038
msgid ""
"Location where the RAID file system is mounted. If it is `/`, the RAID level "
"must be 1 unless a boot partition (`/boot`) is present. If a boot partition "
"is present, the `/boot` partition must be level 1 and the root (`/`) "
"partition can be any of the available types. The _partitions*_ (which "
"denotes that multiple partitions can be listed) lists the RAID identifiers "
"to add to the RAID array."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1039
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1845
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--level=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1040
msgid ""
"RAID level to use (`0`, `1`, `4`, `5`, `6`, or `10`). See xref:install/"
"Installing_Using_Anaconda.adoc#sect-installation-gui-manual-partitioning-"
"filesystems[Device, File System and RAID Types] for information about "
"various RAID types and their requirements."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1041
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1309
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--device=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1042
msgid ""
"Name of the RAID device to use. As of {PRODUCT}{nbsp}{PRODVER}, RAID devices "
"are no longer referred to by names like `md0`. If you have an old (v0.90 "
"metadata) array that you cannot assign a name to, you can specify the array "
"by a filesystem label or UUID (for example, [option]#--device=rhel7-root --"
"label=rhel7-root#)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1043
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--spares=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1044
msgid ""
"Specifies the number of spare drives allocated for the RAID array. Spare "
"drives are used to rebuild the array in case of drive failure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1059
msgid ""
"Specify the label to give to the filesystem to be made. If the given label "
"is already in use by another filesystem, a new label will be created."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1061
msgid "Use an existing RAID device and do not format it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1063
msgid "Use an existing RAID device and reformat it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1065
msgid ""
"Specifies that this array should be encrypted, using the passphrase provided "
"in the [option]#--passphrase# option. If you do not specify a passphrase, "
"[application]*Anaconda* uses the default, system-wide passphrase set with "
"the [command]#autopart --passphrase# command, or stops the installation and "
"prompts you to provide a passphrase if no default is set."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1089
msgid ""
"The following example shows how to create a RAID level 1 partition for `/`, "
"and a RAID level 5 for `/home`, assuming there are three SCSI disks on the "
"system. It also creates three swap partitions, one on each drive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1090
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a RAID array in Kickstart"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1099
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#part raid.01 --size=6000 --ondisk=sda#\n"
"[command]#part raid.02 --size=6000 --ondisk=sdb#\n"
"[command]#part raid.03 --size=6000 --ondisk=sdc#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#part swap --size=512 --ondisk=sda#\n"
"[command]#part swap --size=512 --ondisk=sdb#\n"
"[command]#part swap --size=512 --ondisk=sdc#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1107
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#part raid.11 --size=1 --grow --ondisk=sda#\n"
"[command]#part raid.12 --size=1 --grow --ondisk=sdb#\n"
"[command]#part raid.13 --size=1 --grow --ondisk=sdc#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1110
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#raid / --level=1 --device=f{PRODVER}-root --label=f{PRODVER}-root raid.01 raid.02 raid.03#\n"
"[command]#raid /home --level=5 --device=f{PRODVER}-home --label=f{PRODVER}-home raid.11 raid.12 raid.13#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1116
#, no-wrap
msgid "reqpart (optional) - Create Required Partitions"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1119
msgid ""
"Automatically create partitions required by your hardware platform. These "
"include a `/boot/efi` for x86_64 and Aarch64 systems with UEFI firmware, "
"`biosboot` for x86_64 systems with BIOS firmware and GPT (GUID Partition "
"Table), and `PRePBoot` for IBM Power Systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1124
msgid ""
"This command can not be used together with [command]#autopart#, because "
"[command]#autopart# does the same and creates other partitions or logical "
"volumes such as `/` and `swap` on top. In contrast with [command]#autopart#, "
"this command only creates platform-specific partitions and leaves the rest "
"of the drive empty, allowing you to create a custom layout."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1130
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#reqpart [--add-boot]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1132
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--add-boot#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1133
msgid ""
"Create a separate `/boot` partition in addition to the platform-specific "
"partition created by the base command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1135
#, no-wrap
msgid "volgroup (optional) - Create LVM Volume Group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1138
msgid "Creates a Logical Volume Management (LVM) volume group."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1142
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#volgroup _name_ _partition_ [pass:attributes[{blank}]_options_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1150
msgid ""
"This limitation only applies to newly created logical volume and volume "
"group names. If you are reusing existing ones using the [option]#--noformat# "
"or [option]#--noformat# option, their names will not be changed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1154
msgid ""
"For a detailed partitioning example including [command]#volgroup#, see xref:"
"sect-kickstart-example-advanced-partitioning[Advanced Partitioning Example]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1156
msgid "Use an existing volume group and do not format it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1158
msgid "Use an existing volume group and reformat it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1159
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--pesize=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1160
msgid ""
"Set the size of the physical extents. The default size for Kickstart "
"installations is 4 MiB."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1161
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--reserved-space=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1162
msgid ""
"Specify an amount of space to leave unused in a volume group in megabytes. "
"Applicable only to newly created volume groups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1163
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--reserved-percent=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1164
msgid ""
"Specify a percentage of total volume group space to leave unused. Applicable "
"only to newly created volume groups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1177
#, no-wrap
msgid "zerombr (optional) - Reinitialize Partition Tables"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1180
msgid ""
"If [command]#zerombr# is specified, any invalid partition tables found on "
"disks are initialized. This destroys all of the contents of disks with "
"invalid partition tables. This command is required when performing an "
"unattended installation on a system with previously initialized disks."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1185
msgid ""
"On IBM System{nbsp}z, if [command]#zerombr# is specified, any _Direct Access "
"Storage Device_ (DASD) visible to the installation program which is not "
"already low-level formatted is automatically low-level formatted with "
"[application]*dasdfmt*. The command also prevents user choice during "
"interactive installations."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1187
msgid ""
"If [command]#zerombr# is not specified and there is at least one unformatted "
"DASD visible to the installation program, a non-interactive Kickstart "
"installation will exit unsuccessfully."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1189
msgid ""
"If [command]#zerombr# is not specified and there is at least one unformatted "
"DASD visible to the installation program, an interactive installation exits "
"if the user does not agree to format all visible and unformatted DASDs. To "
"circumvent this, only activate those DASDs that you will use during "
"installation. You can always add more DASDs after installation is complete."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1193
#, no-wrap
msgid "zfcp (optional) - Configure Fibre Channel Device"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1196
msgid ""
"Define a Fibre channel device. This option only applies on IBM System{nbsp}"
"z. All of the options described below must be specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1200
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#zfcp --devnum=pass:attributes[{blank}]_devnum_ --wwpn=pass:attributes[{blank}]_wwpn_ --fcplun=pass:attributes[{blank}]_lun_pass:attributes[{blank}]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1202
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--devnum#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1203
msgid "The device number (zFCP adaptor device bus ID)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1204
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--wwpn#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1205
msgid ""
"The device's World Wide Port Name (WWPN). Takes the form of a 16-digit "
"number, preceded by `0x`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1206
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--fcplun#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1207
msgid ""
"The device's Logical Unit Number (LUN). Takes the form of a 16-digit number, "
"preceded by `0x`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1209
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1326
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1339
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1213
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#zfcp --devnum=0.0.4000 --wwpn=0x5005076300C213e9 --fcplun=0x5022000000000000#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1216
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1219
msgid "Commands in this chapter are used for network configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1221
#, no-wrap
msgid "firewall (optional) - Configure Firewall"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1224
msgid "Specify the firewall configuration for the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1228
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#firewall --enabled | --disabled _device_ [--trust= | --ssh | --smtp | --http | --ftp | --port= | --service=]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1230
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--enabled# or [option]#--enable#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1231
msgid ""
"Reject incoming connections that are not in response to outbound requests, "
"such as DNS replies or DHCP requests. If access to services running on this "
"machine is needed, you can choose to allow specific services through the "
"firewall."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1232
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--disabled# or [option]#--disable#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1233
msgid "Disable the firewall."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1234
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--trust=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1235
msgid ""
"Listing a device here, such as `em1`, allows all traffic coming to and from "
"that device to go through the firewall. To list more than one device, use "
"this option again - for example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1239
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#firewall --enable --trust=em1 --trust=em2#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1242
msgid "Do not use a comma-separated format such as [option]#--trust em1, em2#."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1243
#, no-wrap
msgid "_incoming_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1244
msgid ""
"Replace with one or more of the following to allow the specified services "
"through the firewall:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1246
msgid "[option]#--ssh#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1248
msgid "[option]#--smtp#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1250
msgid "[option]#--http#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1252
msgid "[option]#--ftp#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1254
msgid ""
"You can specify that ports be allowed through the firewall using the port:"
"protocol format. For example, to allow IMAP access through your firewall, "
"specify `imap:tcp`. Numeric ports can also be specified explicitly; for "
"example, to allow UDP packets on port 1234 through, specify `1234:udp`. To "
"specify multiple ports, separate them by commas."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1255
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--service=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1256
msgid ""
"This option provides a higher-level way to allow services through the "
"firewall. Some services (like `cups`, `avahi`, etc.) require multiple ports "
"to be open or other special configuration in order for the service to work. "
"You can specify each individual port with the [option]#--port# option, or "
"specify [command]#--service=# and open them all at once."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1258
msgid ""
"Valid options are anything recognized by the [application]*firewall-offline-"
"cmd* program in the [package]*firewalld* package. If `firewalld` is running, "
"[command]#firewall-cmd --get-services# will provide a list of known service "
"names."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1260
#, no-wrap
msgid "network (optional) - Configure Network Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1263
msgid ""
"Configures network information for the target system and activates network "
"devices in the installation environment. The device specified in the first "
"[command]#network# command is activated automatically. Activation of the "
"device can be also explicitly required by the [option]#--activate# option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1264
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--activate#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1265
msgid ""
"If you use the [option]#--activate# option on a device that has already been "
"activated (for example, an interface you configured with boot options so "
"that the system could retrieve the Kickstart file) the device is reactivated "
"to use the details specified in the Kickstart file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1267
msgid ""
"Use the [option]#--nodefroute# option to prevent the device from using the "
"default route."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1268
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--no-activate#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1269
msgid "Prevents the configured device from automatically activating on boot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1270
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--bootproto=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1271
msgid ""
"One of `dhcp`, `bootp`, `ibft`, or `static`. The default option is "
"`dhcp`pass:attributes[{blank}]; the `dhcp` and `bootp` options are treated "
"the same."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1273
msgid ""
"The DHCP method uses a DHCP server system to obtain its networking "
"configuration. The BOOTP method is similar, requiring a BOOTP server to "
"supply the networking configuration. To direct a system to use DHCP:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1277
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --bootproto=dhcp#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1280
msgid ""
"To direct a machine to use BOOTP to obtain its networking configuration, use "
"the following line in the Kickstart file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1284
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --bootproto=bootp#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1287
msgid "To direct a machine to use the configuration specified in iBFT, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1291
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --bootproto=ibft#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1294
msgid ""
"The `static` method requires that you specify the IP address, netmask, "
"gateway, and nameserver in the Kickstart file. This information is static "
"and is used during and after the installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1296
msgid ""
"All static networking configuration information must be specified on *one* "
"line; you cannot wrap lines using a backslash (`\\`) as you can on a command "
"line."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1300
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --bootproto=static --ip=10.0.2.15 --netmask=255.255.255.0 --gateway=10.0.2.254 --nameserver=10.0.2.1#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1303
msgid ""
"You can also configure multiple nameservers at the same time. To do so, use "
"the [option]#--nameserver=# options once for each name server you want to "
"configure:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1307
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1375
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --bootproto=static --ip=10.0.2.15 --netmask=255.255.255.0 --gateway=10.0.2.254 --nameserver=192.168.2.1 --nameserver=192.168.3.1#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1310
msgid ""
"Specifies the device to be configured (and eventually activated in "
"[application]*Anaconda*) with the [command]#network# command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1312
msgid ""
"If the [option]#--device=# option is missing on the *first* use of the "
"[command]#network# command, the value of the [option]#ksdevice=# "
"[application]*Anaconda* boot option is used, if available. Note that this is "
"considered deprecated behavior; in most cases, you should always specify a "
"[option]#--device=# for every [command]#network# command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1314
msgid ""
"The behavior of any subsequent [command]#network# command in the same "
"Kickstart file is unspecified if its [option]#--device=# option is missing. "
"Make sure you specify this option for any [command]#network# command beyond "
"the first."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1316
msgid "You can specify a device to be activated in any of the following ways:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1318
msgid "the device name of the interface, for example, `em1`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1320
msgid "the MAC address of the interface, for example, `01:23:45:67:89:ab`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1322
msgid ""
"the keyword `link`, which specifies the first interface with its link in the "
"`up` state"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1324
msgid ""
"the keyword `bootif`, which uses the MAC address that "
"[application]*pxelinux* set in the `BOOTIF` variable. Set `IPAPPEND 2` in "
"your `pxelinux.cfg` file to have [application]*pxelinux* set the `BOOTIF` "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1330
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --bootproto=dhcp --device=em1#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1332
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--bindto=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1333
msgid ""
"Optional. Allows to specify how the connection configuration created for the "
"device should be bound. If the option is not used, the connection binds to "
"interface name (`DEVICE` value in ifcfg file). For virtual devices (bond, "
"team, bridge) it configures binding of slaves. Not applicable to vlan "
"devices."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1335
msgid ""
"Note that this option is independent of how the `--device` is specified."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1337
msgid ""
"Currently only the value `mac` is suported. `--bindto=mac` will bind the "
"connection to MAC address of the device (`HWADDR` value in the `ifcfg` file)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1343
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --device=01:23:45:67:89:ab --bootproto=dhcp --bindto=mac#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1346
msgid ""
"The above will bind the configuration of the device specified by MAC address "
"`01:23:45:67:89:ab` to its MAC address."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1350
#, no-wrap
msgid "network --device=01:23:45:67:89:ab --bootproto=dhcp\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1352
msgid ""
"The above will bind the configuration of the device specified by MAC address "
"`01:23:45:67:89:ab` to its interface name (e.g. `ens3`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1356
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --device=ens3 --bootproto=dhcp --bindto=mac#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1359
msgid ""
"The above will bind the configuration of the device specified by interface "
"name `ens3` to its MAC address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1360
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ip=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1361
msgid "IP address of the device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1362
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ipv6=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1363
msgid ""
"IPv6 address of the device, in the form of _address_pass:attributes[{blank}]"
"[/pass:attributes[{blank}]_prefix_ _length_pass:attributes[{blank}]] - for "
"example, `3ffe:ffff:0:1::1/128` . If _prefix_ is omitted, `64` will be used. "
"You can also use `auto` for automatic configuration, or `dhcp` for DHCPv6-"
"only configuration (no router advertisements)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1364
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--gateway=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1365
msgid "Default gateway as a single IPv4 address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1366
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ipv6gateway=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1367
msgid "Default gateway as a single IPv6 address."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1368
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nodefroute#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1369
msgid ""
"Prevents the interface being set as the default route. Use this option when "
"you activate additional devices with the [option]#--activate=# option, for "
"example, a NIC on a separate subnet for an iSCSI target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1370
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nameserver=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1371
msgid ""
"DNS name server, as an IP address. To specify more than one name server, use "
"this parameter multiple times. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1377
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nodns#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1378
msgid "Do not configure any DNS server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1379
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--netmask=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1380
msgid "Network mask for the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1381
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--hostname=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1382
msgid ""
"Host name for the installed system. The host name can be either a _fully-"
"qualified domain name_ (FQDN) in the format _hostname_._domainname_, or a "
"short host name with no domain name. Many networks have a _Dynamic Host "
"Configuration Protocol_ (`DHCP`) service that automatically supplies "
"connected systems with a domain name; to allow the `DHCP` service to assign "
"the domain name to this machine, only specify the short host name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1383
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ethtool=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1384
msgid ""
"Specifies additional low-level settings for the network device which will be "
"passed to the [application]*ethtool* program."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1385
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--essid=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1386
msgid "The network ID for wireless networks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1387
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--wepkey=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1388
msgid "The WEP encryption key for wireless networks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1389
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--wpakey=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1390
msgid "The WPA encryption key for wireless networks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1391
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--onboot=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1392
msgid "Whether or not to enable the device at boot time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1393
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--dhcpclass=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1394
msgid "The DHCP class."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1395
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--mtu=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1396
msgid "The MTU of the device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1397
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--noipv4#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1398
msgid "Disable IPv4 on this device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1399
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--noipv6#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1400
msgid "Disable IPv6 on this device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1401
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--bondslaves=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1402
msgid ""
"When this option is used, the network device specified in the [option]#--"
"device=# option will be created using slaves defined in the [option]#--"
"bondslaves=# option. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1406
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --device=mynetwork --bondslaves=em1,em2#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1409
msgid ""
"The above command will create a bond device named `mynetwork` using the "
"`em1` and `em2` interfaces as its slaves."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1410
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#--bondopts=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1411
msgid ""
"A list of optional parameters for a bonded interface, which is specified "
"using the [command]#--bondslaves=# and [command]#--device=# options. Options "
"in this list must be separated by commas (\"pass:attributes[{blank}]`,`pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]\") or semicolons (\"pass:attributes[{blank}]`;`pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]\"). If an option itself contains a comma, use a "
"semicolon to separate the options. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1415
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --bondopts=mode=active-backup,balance-rr;primary=eth1#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1418
msgid ""
"Available optional parameters are listed in the [citetitle]_Working with "
"Kernel Modules_ chapter of the [citetitle]_Fedora System Administrator's "
"Guide_, available at link:++https://docs.fedoraproject.org/++[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1423
msgid ""
"The [option]#--bondopts=mode=# parameter only supports full mode names such "
"as `balance-rr` or `broadcast`, not their numerical representations such as "
"`0` or `3`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1426
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--vlanid=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1427
msgid ""
"Specifies virtual LAN (VLAN) ID number (802.1q tag) for the device created "
"using the device specified in [option]#--device=# as a parent. For example, "
"[command]#network --device=em1 --vlanid=171# will create a virtual LAN "
"device `em1.171`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1428
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--interfacename=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1429
msgid ""
"Specify a custom interface name for a virtual LAN device. This option should "
"be used when the default name generated by the [option]#--vlanid=# option is "
"not desirable. This option must be used along with [option]#--vlanid=#. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1433
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --device=em1 --vlanid=171 --interfacename=vlan171#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1436
msgid ""
"The above command will create a virtual LAN interface named `vlan171` on the "
"`em1` device with an ID of `171`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1438
msgid ""
"The interface name can be arbitrary (for example, `my-vlan`), but in "
"specific cases, the following conventions must be followed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1440
msgid ""
"If the name contains a dot (`.`), it must take the form of `pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]_NAME_._ID_pass:attributes[{blank}]`. The _NAME_ is "
"arbitrary, but the _ID_ must be the VLAN ID. For example: `em1.171` or `my-"
"vlan.171`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1442
msgid ""
"Names starting with `vlan` must take the form of `vlanpass:"
"attributes[{blank}]_ID_pass:attributes[{blank}]` - for example, `vlan171`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1443
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--teamslaves=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1444
msgid ""
"Team device specified by the [option]#--device=# option will be created "
"using slaves specified in this option. Slaves are separated by commas. A "
"slave can be followed by its configuration, which is a single-quoted JSON "
"string with double quotes escaped by the `\\` character. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1448
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --teamslaves=\"p3p1'{\\\"prio\\\": -10, \\\"sticky\\\": true}',p3p2'{\\\"prio\\\": 100}'\"#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1451
msgid "See also the [option]#--teamconfig=# option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1452
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--teamconfig=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1453
msgid ""
"Double-quoted team device configuration which is a single-quoted JSON string "
"with double quotes escaped by the `\\` character. The device name is "
"specified by [option]#--device=# option and its slaves and their "
"configuration by [option]#--teamslaves=# option. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1458
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --device team0 --activate --bootproto static --ip=10.34.102.222 --netmask=255.255.255.0 --gateway=10.34.102.254 --nameserver=10.34.39.2 --teamslaves=\"p3p1'{\\\"prio\\\": -10, \\\"sticky\\\": true}',p3p2'{\\\"prio\\\": 100}'\" --teamconfig=\"{\\\"runner\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"activebackup\\\"}}\"#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1461
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--bridgeslaves=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1462
msgid ""
"When this option is used, the network bridge with device name specified "
"using the [option]#--device=# option will be created and devices defined in "
"the [option]#--bridgeslaves=# option will be added to the bridge. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1466
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#network --device=bridge0 --bridgeslaves=em1#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1468
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--bridgeopts=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1469
msgid ""
"An optional comma-separated list of parameters for the bridged interface. "
"Available values are `stp`, `priority`, `forward-delay`, `hello-time`, `max-"
"age`, and `ageing-time`. For information about these parameters, see the "
"[citetitle]_bridge setting_ table in the `nm-settings(5)` man page or at "
"link:++https://developer.gnome.org/NetworkManager/0.9/ref-settings.html++[]. "
"Also see the [citetitle]_{PRODUCT} Networking Guide_, available at link:+"
"+https://docs.fedoraproject.org/++[], for general information about network "
"bridging."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1471
#, no-wrap
msgid "Console and Environment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1474
msgid ""
"The following commands control the environment of the system after the "
"installation finishes - language, keyboard layouts, or the graphical "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1476
#, no-wrap
msgid "keyboard (optional) - Configure Keyboard Layouts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1479
msgid "Sets one or more available keyboard layouts for the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1483
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#keyboard --vckeymap= | --xlayouts= [--switch=]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1485
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--vckeymap=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1486
msgid ""
"Specify a `VConsole` keymap which should be used. Valid names correspond to "
"the list of files in the `/usr/lib/kbd/keymaps/*` directory, without the `."
"map.gz` extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1487
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--xlayouts=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1488
msgid ""
"Specify a list of [application]*X* layouts that should be used as a comma-"
"separated list without spaces. Accepts values in the same format as "
"`setxkbmap(1)`, either in the `pass:attributes[{blank}]_layout_pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]` format (such as `cz`), or in the `pass:"
"attributes[{blank}]_layout_ (_variant_)` format (such as `cz (qwerty)`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1490
msgid ""
"All available layouts can be viewed on the `xkeyboard-config(7)` man page "
"under `Layouts`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1491
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--switch=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1492
msgid ""
"Specify a list of layout-switching options (shortcuts for switching between "
"multiple keyboard layouts). Multiple options must be separated by commas "
"without spaces. Accepts values in the same format as `setxkbmap(1)`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1494
msgid ""
"Available switching options can be viewed on the `xkeyboard-config(7)` man "
"page under `Options`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1496
msgid ""
"The following example sets up two keyboard layouts (`English (US)` and "
"`Czech (qwerty)`) using the [option]#--xlayouts=# option, and allows to "
"switch between them using kbd:[Alt + Shift]:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1499
#, no-wrap
msgid "keyboard --xlayouts=us,'cz (qwerty)' --switch=grp:alt_shift_toggle\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1502
#, no-wrap
msgid "lang (optional) - Configure Language During Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1505
msgid ""
"Sets the language to use during installation and the default language to use "
"on the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1509
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#lang _language_ [--addsupport=]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1512
msgid ""
"The file `/usr/share/system-config-language/locale-list` provides a list of "
"the valid _language_ codes in the first column of each line and is part of "
"the [package]*system-config-language* package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1514
msgid ""
"Certain languages (for example, Chinese, Japanese, Korean, and Indic "
"languages) are not supported during text-mode installation. If you specify "
"one of these languages with the [command]#lang# command and use text mode, "
"the installation process will continue in English, but the installed system "
"will use your selection as its default language."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1515
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--addsupport=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1516
msgid ""
"Add support for additional languages. Takes the form of comma-separated list "
"without spaces. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1519
#, no-wrap
msgid "lang en_US --addsupport=cs_CZ,de_DE,en_UK\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1522
#, no-wrap
msgid "services (optional) - Configure Services"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1525
msgid ""
"Modifies the default set of services that will run under the default "
"[application]*systemd* target. The list of disabled services is processed "
"before the list of enabled services - therefore, if a service appears on "
"both lists, it will be enabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1529
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#services [--disabled=pass:attributes[{blank}]_list_pass:attributes[{blank}]] [--enabled=pass:attributes[{blank}]_list_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1532
msgid ""
"Do not include spaces in the list of services. If you do, Kickstart will "
"enable or disable only the services up to the first space. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1536
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#services --disabled=auditd, cups,smartd, nfslock#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1539
msgid ""
"The above will disable only the `auditd` service. To disable all four "
"services, the entry should include no spaces:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1543
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#services --disabled=auditd,cups,smartd,nfslock#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1545
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--disabled=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1546
msgid "Disable the services given in the comma separated list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1547
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--enabled=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1548
msgid "Enable the services given in the comma separated list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1550
#, no-wrap
msgid "skipx (optional) - Do Not Configure X Window System"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1553
msgid ""
"If present, [application]*X* will not be configured on the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1558
msgid ""
"If you install a display manager among your package selection options, this "
"package will create an [application]*X* configuration, and the installed "
"system will default to `graphical.target`. The effect of the "
"[command]#skipx# option will be overridden."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1562
#, no-wrap
msgid "timezone (optional) - Configure Time Zone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1565
msgid ""
"Sets the system time zone to _timezone_. To view a list of available time "
"zones, use the [command]#timedatectl list-timezones# command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1567
msgid ""
"Every option, including actually specifying a time zone, is optional "
"starting with Fedora 25. This allows you to, for example, disable NTP from "
"starting using [option]#--nontp# without having to choose any time zone. "
"However, if this command is present in the Kickstart file, at least one "
"option must be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1571
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#timezone [pass:attributes[{blank}]_timezone_pass:attributes[{blank}]] [pass:attributes[{blank}]_options_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1573
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--utc#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1574
msgid ""
"If present, the system assumes the hardware clock is set to UTC (Greenwich "
"Mean) time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1575
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nontp#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1576
msgid "Disable the NTP service automatic starting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1577
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ntpservers=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1578
msgid ""
"Specify a list of NTP servers to be used as a comma-separated list without "
"spaces."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1580
#, no-wrap
msgid "xconfig (optional) - Configure X Window System"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1583
msgid ""
"Configures the [application]*X Window System*. If you install the "
"[application]*X Window System* with a Kickstart file that does not include "
"the [command]#xconfig# command, you must provide the [application]*X* "
"configuration manually during installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1585
msgid ""
"Do not use this command in a Kickstart file that does not install the "
"[application]*X Window System*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1586
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--defaultdesktop=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1587
msgid ""
"Specify either `GNOME` or `KDE` to set the default desktop (assumes that "
"[application]*GNOME Desktop Environment* and/or [application]*KDE Desktop "
"Environment* has been installed in the [command]#%packages# section)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1588
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--startxonboot#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1589
msgid "Use a graphical login on the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1591
#, no-wrap
msgid "Users, Groups and Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1594
msgid ""
"The commands below are used to control user accounts, groups, and related "
"areas."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1596
#, no-wrap
msgid "auth or authconfig (optional) - Configure Authentication (deprecated)"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1601
msgid ""
"This command has been deprecated by [command]#authselect#. Using it will "
"invoke the authconfig compatibility tool; however, it is highly recommended "
"to use [command]#authselect# instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1604
msgid ""
"Sets up the authentication options for the system using the "
"[command]#authconfig# command, which can also be run on a command line after "
"the installation finishes. See the `authconfig(8)` manual page and the "
"[command]#authconfig --help# command for more details. Passwords are "
"shadowed by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1606
#, no-wrap
msgid "authselect (optional) - Configure Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1609
msgid ""
"This command sets up the authentication options for the system. This is just "
"a wrapper around the [command]#authselect# program, so all options "
"recognized by that program are valid for this command. See the "
"`authselect(8)` for a complete list. Passwords are shadowed by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1612
#, no-wrap
msgid "group (optional) - Create User Group"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1615
msgid ""
"Creates a new user group on the system. If a group with the given name or "
"GID already exists, this command will fail. In addition, the [command]#user# "
"command can be used to create a new group for the newly created user."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1619
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#group --name=pass:attributes[{blank}]_name_ [--gid=pass:attributes[{blank}]_gid_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1622
msgid "Provides the name of the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1623
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1786
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--gid=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1624
msgid ""
"The group ID (GID). If not provided, defaults to the next available non-"
"system GID."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1626
#, no-wrap
msgid "pwpolicy (optional) - Change the Default Password Policy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1629
msgid ""
"This command can be used to set custom requirements (policy) such as length "
"and strength for passwords set during the installation - the `root` "
"password, user passwords and LUKS (disk encryption) password."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1634
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#pwpolicy _name_ [--minlen=pass:attributes[{blank}]_length_pass:attributes[{blank}]] [--minquality=pass:attributes[{blank}]_quality_pass:attributes[{blank}]] [--strict|nostrict] [--emptyok|noempty] [--changesok|nochanges]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1638
msgid ""
"The `libpwquality` library is used to check minimum password requirements "
"(length and quality). You can use the [command]#pwscore# and "
"[command]#pwmake# commands provided by the [package]*libpwquality* package "
"to check the quality score of your chosen password, or to create a random "
"password with a given score. See the `pwscore(1)` and `pwmake(1)` man pages "
"for details about these commands."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1643
msgid ""
"This command must be used inside the [command]#%anaconda# section. See xref:"
"sect-kickstart-commands-anaconda[%anaconda (optional) - Additional Anaconda "
"Configuration] for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1646
#, no-wrap
msgid "_name_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1647
msgid ""
"Name of the password entry. Supported values are `root`, `user` and `luks` "
"for `root` password, user passwords and LUKS password, respectively."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1648
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--minlen=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1649
msgid ""
"Sets the minimum allowed password length. The default minimum length is `8`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1650
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--minquality=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1651
msgid ""
"Sets the minimum allowed password quality as defined by the `libpwquality` "
"library. The default value is `50`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1652
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--strict#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1653
msgid ""
"Strict password enforcement. Passwords not meeting the quality requirements "
"specified in [option]#--minquality=# will not be allowed. Enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1654
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--notstrict#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1655
msgid ""
"Passwords *not* meeting the minimum quality requirements specified in "
"[option]#--minquality=# will be allowed after `Done` is clicked twice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1656
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--emptyok#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1657
msgid "Allow empty passwords. Enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1658
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--notempty#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1659
msgid "Do not allow empty passwords."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1660
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--changesok#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1661
msgid ""
"Allow changing the password in the user interface, even if the Kickstart "
"file already specifies a password."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1662
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nochanges#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1663
msgid ""
"Do not allow changing passwords which are already set in the Kickstart file. "
"Enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1665
msgid "An example use of the [command]#pwpolicy# command is below:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1672
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#%anaconda#\n"
"[command]#pwpolicy root --minlen=10 --minquality=60 --strict --notempty --nochanges#\n"
"[command]#%end#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1676
#, no-wrap
msgid "realm (optional) - Join an Active Directory or IPA Domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1679
msgid ""
"Join an Active Directory or IPA domain. For more information about this "
"command, see the [command]#join# section of the `realm(8)` man page."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1683
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#realm join _domain_ [pass:attributes[{blank}]_options_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1685
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--computer-ou=OU=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1686
msgid ""
"Provide the _distinguished name_ of an organizational unit in order to "
"create the computer account. The exact format of the distinguished name "
"depends on the client software and membership software. The root DSE portion "
"of the distinguished name can usually be left out."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1687
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--no-password#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1688
msgid "Join automatically without a password."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1689
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--one-time-password=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1690
msgid ""
"Join using a one-time password. This is not possible with all types of realm."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1691
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--client-software=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1692
msgid ""
"Only join realms which can run this client software. Valid values include "
"`sssd` and `winbind`. Not all realms support all values. By default, the "
"client software is chosen automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1693
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--server-software=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1694
msgid ""
"Only join realms which can run this server software. Possible values include "
"`active-directory` or `freeipa`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1695
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--membership-software=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1696
msgid ""
"Use this software when joining the realm. Valid values include `samba` and "
"`adcli`. Not all realms support all values. By default, the membership "
"software is chosen automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1698
#, no-wrap
msgid "rootpw (required) - Set Root Password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1701
msgid "Sets the system's root password to the _password_ argument."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1705
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#rootpw [--iscrypted|--plaintext] [--lock] _password_pass:attributes[{blank}]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1708
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1772
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1891
msgid ""
"If this option is present, the password argument is assumed to already be "
"encrypted. This option is mutually exclusive with [option]#--plaintext#. To "
"create an encrypted password, you can use Python:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1712
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1776
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1895
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ [command]#python -c 'import crypt; print(crypt.crypt(\"My Password\", \"$6$My Salt\"))'#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1715
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1779
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1898
msgid ""
"This will generate a SHA512 crypt of your password using your provided salt."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1716
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1780
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1899
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--plaintext#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1717
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1781
msgid ""
"If this option is present, the password argument is assumed to be in plain "
"text. This option is mutually exclusive with [option]#--iscrypted#."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1718
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1767
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1901
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--lock#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1719
msgid ""
"If this option is present, the root account is locked by default. This means "
"that the root user will not be able to log in from the console."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1721
#, no-wrap
msgid "selinux (optional) - Configure SELinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1724
msgid ""
"Sets the state of SELinux on the installed system. The default policy is "
"`enforcing`. For more information regarding SELinux in {PRODUCT}, see the "
"[citetitle]_{PRODUCT} SELinux User's and Administrator's Guide_, available "
"at link:++https://docs.fedoraproject.org/++[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1728
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#selinux [--disabled|--enforcing|--permissive]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1730
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--enforcing#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1731
msgid "Enables SELinux with the default targeted policy being `enforcing`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1732
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--permissive#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1733
msgid ""
"Enables SELinux with the default targeted policy being `permissive`. This "
"policy outputs warnings based on the SELinux policy, but does not actually "
"enforce the policy."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1735
msgid "Disables SELinux completely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1737
#, no-wrap
msgid "sshkey (optional) - Add an Authorized SSH Key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1740
msgid ""
"Use this command to add a specified `SSH` key to an user's `authorized_keys` "
"file. The specified user must either be `root`, or it must be created in the "
"Kickstart file - either automatically by an installed package, or using xref:"
"sect-kickstart-commands-user[user (optional) - Create User Account]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1743
#, no-wrap
msgid "sshkey --username=user \"ssh_key\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1746
msgid ""
"The _ssh_key_ must be a full `SSH` key fingerprint, and it must be enclosed "
"in quotes (`\"\"`) because the key may contain spaces."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1747
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--username=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1748
msgid ""
"The name of the user account to which you want to install the `SSH` key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1750
#, no-wrap
msgid "user (optional) - Create User Account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1753
msgid "Creates a new user on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1757
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#user --name=pass:attributes[{blank}]_username_ [pass:attributes[{blank}]_options_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1760
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1889
msgid "Provides the name of the user. This option is required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1761
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--gecos=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1762
msgid ""
"Provides the GECOS information for the user. This is a string of various "
"system-specific fields separated by a comma. It is frequently used to "
"specify the user's full name, office number, etc. See the `passwd(5)` man "
"page for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1763
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--groups=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1764
msgid ""
"In addition to the default group, a comma separated list of group names the "
"user should belong to. The groups must exist before the user account is "
"created. See xref:sect-kickstart-commands-group[group (optional) - Create "
"User Group]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1765
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--homedir=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1766
msgid ""
"The home directory for the user. If not provided, this defaults to `/home/"
"pass:attributes[{blank}]_username_pass:attributes[{blank}]`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1768
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1902
msgid ""
"If this option is present, this account is locked by default. This means "
"that the user will not be able to log in from the console."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1770
msgid ""
"The new user's password. If no password is provided, the account will be "
"locked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1782
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--shell=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1783
msgid ""
"The user's login shell. If not provided, the system default will be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1784
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--uid=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1785
msgid ""
"The _UID_ (User ID). If not provided, this defaults to the next available "
"non-system UID."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1787
msgid ""
"The _GID_ (Group ID) to be used for the user's default group. If not "
"provided, this defaults to the next available non-system group ID."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1789
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation Environment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1792
msgid ""
"The following commands control how the system will behave during the "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1794
#, no-wrap
msgid "autostep (optional) - Go Through Every Screen"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1797
msgid ""
"Normally, Kickstart installations skip unnecessary screens. This option "
"makes the installation program step through every screen, displaying each "
"briefly. This option should not be used when deploying a system because it "
"may disrupt package installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1801
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#autostep [--autoscreenshot]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1803
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--autoscreenshot#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1804
msgid ""
"Take a screenshot at every step during installation. These screenshots are "
"stored in `/tmp/anaconda-screenshots` during the installation, and after the "
"installation finishes you can find them in `/root/anaconda-screenshots`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1806
msgid ""
"Each screen is only captured right before the installer switches to the next "
"one. This is important, because if you do not use all required Kickstart "
"options and the installation therefore does not begin automatically, you can "
"go to the screens which were not automatically configured, perform any "
"configuration you want. Then, when you press `Done` to continue, the screen "
"will be captured including the configuration you just provided."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1808
#, no-wrap
msgid "cmdline (optional) - Perform Installation in Command Line Mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1811
msgid ""
"Perform the installation in a completely non-interactive command line mode. "
"Any prompts for interaction halts the install. This mode is useful on IBM "
"System{nbsp}z systems with the x3270 terminal."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1816
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1828
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1912
msgid ""
"For a fully automatic installation, you must either specify one of the "
"available modes ([command]#graphical#, [command]#text#, or "
"[command]#cmdline#) in the Kickstart file, or you must use the "
"[option]#console=# boot option as described in xref:advanced/Boot_Options."
"adoc#sect-boot-options-display[Console, Environment and Display Options]. "
"Otherwise the system will halt and ask you to choose a mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1820
#, no-wrap
msgid "graphical (optional) - Perform Installation in Graphical Mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1823
msgid ""
"Perform the installation in graphical mode. This is the default. This "
"command takes no options."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1832
#, no-wrap
msgid "logging (optional) - Configure Error Logging During Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1835
msgid ""
"Controls the error logging of [application]*Anaconda* during installation. "
"It has no effect on the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1839
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#logging [--host= | --port= | --level=]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1841
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1932
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--host=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1842
msgid ""
"Send logging information to the given remote host, which must be running a "
"`syslogd` process configured to accept remote logging."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1844
msgid ""
"If the remote syslogd process uses a port other than the default, it may be "
"specified with this option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1846
msgid ""
"Specify the minimum level of messages that appear on virtual console 3 "
"(`tty3`). This only affects messages printed to the console; log files will "
"contain messages of all levels. Possible values are `debug`, `info`, "
"`warning`, `error`, or `critical`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1848
#, no-wrap
msgid "rescue (optional) - Rescue Mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1851
msgid ""
"Automatically enters the installation program's rescue mode. This gives you "
"a chance to repair the system in case of any problems."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1855
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#rescue [--nomount|--romount]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1857
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nomount# or [option]#--romount#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1858
msgid ""
"Controls how the installed system is mounted in the rescue environment. By "
"default, the installation program will find your system and mount it in read-"
"write mode, telling you where it has performed this mount. You may "
"optionally choose to not mount anything (the [option]#--nomount# option) or "
"mount in read-only mode (the [option]#--romount# option). Only one of these "
"two options may be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1860
#, no-wrap
msgid "sshpw (optional) - Restrict ssh Access During Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1863
msgid ""
"During the installation, you can interact with the installation program and "
"monitor its progress over an `SSH` connection. Use the [command]#sshpw# "
"command to create temporary accounts through which to log on. Each instance "
"of the command creates a separate account that exists only in the "
"installation environment. These accounts are not transferred to the "
"installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1867
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#sshpw --username=pass:attributes[{blank}]_name_ _password_ [--iscrypted|--plaintext] [--lock]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1873
msgid ""
"By default, the `ssh` server is not started during the installation. To make "
"`ssh` available during the installation, boot the system with the kernel "
"boot option [option]#inst.sshd#. See xref:advanced/Boot_Options.adoc#sect-"
"boot-options-display[Console, Environment and Display Options] for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1880
msgid ""
"If you want to disable root `ssh` access to your hardware during "
"installation, use the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1884
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#sshpw --username=root --lock#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1888
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--username#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1900
msgid ""
"If this option is present, the password argument is assumed to be in plain "
"text. This option is mutually exclusive with [option]#--iscrypted#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1904
#, no-wrap
msgid "text (optional) - Perform Installation in Text Mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1907
msgid ""
"Perform the Kickstart installation in text mode. Kickstart installations are "
"performed in graphical mode by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1916
#, no-wrap
msgid "unsupported_hardware (optional) - Suppress Unsupported Hardware Alerts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1919
msgid ""
"Suppress the `Unsupported Hardware Detected` alert. If this command is not "
"included and unsupported hardware is detected, the installation will stall "
"at this alert."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1921
#, no-wrap
msgid "vnc (optional) - Configure VNC Access"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1924
msgid ""
"Allows the graphical installation to be viewed remotely via VNC. This method "
"is usually preferred over text mode, as there are some size and language "
"limitations in text installations. With no additional options, this command "
"will start a VNC server on the installation system with no password and will "
"display the details required to connect to it."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1928
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#vnc [--host=pass:attributes[{blank}]_hostname_pass:attributes[{blank}]] [--port=pass:attributes[{blank}]_port_pass:attributes[{blank}]] [--password=pass:attributes[{blank}]_password_pass:attributes[{blank}]]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1931
msgid ""
"For more information about VNC installations, including instructions on how "
"to connect to the installation system, see xref:advanced/VNC_Installations."
"adoc#chap-vnc-installations[Installing Using VNC]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1933
msgid "Connect to a VNC viewer listening on the given hostname."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1935
msgid ""
"Provide a port that the remote VNC viewer process is listening on. If not "
"provided, the VNC default (`5900`) will be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1937
msgid ""
"Set a password which must be provided to connect to the VNC session. This is "
"optional, but recommended."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1939
#, no-wrap
msgid "After the Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1942
msgid ""
"This section contains commands which control the system's behavior "
"immediately after the installation finishes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1944
#, no-wrap
msgid "%addon com_redhat_kdump (optional) - Configure kdump"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1947
msgid ""
"This command configures the [application]*kdump* kernel crash dumping "
"mechanism."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1952
msgid ""
"The syntax for this command is unusual because it is an add-on rather than a "
"built-in Kickstart command. For more information about add-ons, see xref:"
"sect-kickstart-commands-addon[%addon (optional) - Include an Anaconda Add-"
"on]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1956
msgid ""
"[application]*Kdump* is a kernel crash dumping mechanism that allows you to "
"save the contents of the system's memory for later analysis. It relies on "
"[application]*kexec*, which can be used to start a Linux kernel from the "
"context of another kernel without rebooting the system and preserve the "
"contents of the first kernel memory that would otherwise be lost."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1958
msgid ""
"In case of a system crash, [application]*kexec* starts a second kernel (a "
"_capture kernel_). This capture kernel resides in a reserved part of the "
"system memory that is inaccessible to the main kernel. [application]*Kdump* "
"then captures the contents of the crashed kernel's memory (a _crash dump_) "
"and saves it to a specified location. This location can not be configured "
"using Kickstart; it must be specified after the installation by editing the "
"`/etc/kdump.conf` configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1960
msgid "Available options are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1961
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--enable#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1962
msgid "Enable [application]*Kdump* on the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1963
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--disable#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1964
msgid "Do not enable [application]*Kdump* on the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1965
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--reserve-mb=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1966
msgid ""
"The amount of memory you want to reserve for [application]*Kdump* in "
"megabytes. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1970
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"%addon com_redhat_kdump --enable --reserve-mb=128\n"
"%end\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1973
msgid ""
"You can also specify `auto` instead of a numeric value. In that case the "
"installer will determine the amount of RAM to reserve for kdump "
"automatically, based on your system architecture and the total amount of "
"memory on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1975
msgid ""
"If you enable [application]*Kdump* and do not specify the [option]#--reserve-"
"mb=# option, the `auto` value will be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1976
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--enablefadump#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1977
msgid ""
"Enable firmware-assisted dumping on systems which allow it (notably IBM "
"Power{nbsp}Systems servers)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1979
#, no-wrap
msgid "firstboot (optional) - Enable or Disable Initial Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1982
msgid ""
"Determine whether the [application]*Initial Setup* application starts the "
"first time the system is booted. If enabled, the [package]*initial-setup* "
"package must be installed. If not specified, this option is disabled by "
"default. For more information about [application]*Initial Setup*, see xref:"
"install/After_Installation.adoc#sect-initial-setup[Initial Setup]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1986
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#firstboot --enable|--disable [--reconfig]#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1988
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--enable# or [option]#--enabled#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1989
msgid ""
"[application]*Initial Setup* will be started the first time the installed "
"system boots."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1990
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--disable# or [option]#--disabled#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1991
msgid "[application]*Initial Setup* will be disabled."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1992
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--reconfig#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1993
msgid ""
"[application]*Initial Setup* will start after the reboot in reconfiguration "
"mode. This mode enables the language, mouse, keyboard, root password, "
"security level, time zone and networking configuration options in addition "
"to the default ones."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1995
#, no-wrap
msgid "halt (optional) - Halt System After Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:1998
msgid ""
"Halt the system after the installation has successfully completed. This is "
"similar to a manual installation, where after the installation finishes, the "
"installer displays a message and waits for the user to press a key before "
"rebooting. During a Kickstart installation, if no completion method is "
"specified, this option is used as the default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2000
msgid ""
"For other completion methods, see the [command]#poweroff#, "
"[command]#reboot#, and [command]#shutdown# commands."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2002
#, no-wrap
msgid "poweroff (optional) - Power Off After Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2005
msgid ""
"Shut down and power off the system after the installation has successfully "
"completed."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2010
msgid ""
"The [command]#poweroff# command is highly dependent on the system hardware "
"in use. Specifically, certain hardware components such as the BIOS, APM "
"(advanced power management), and ACPI (advanced configuration and power "
"interface) must be able to interact with the system kernel. Consult your "
"hardware documentation for more information on you system's APM/ACPI "
"abilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2014
msgid ""
"For other completion methods, see the [command]#halt#, [command]#reboot#, "
"and [command]#shutdown# Kickstart commands."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2016
#, no-wrap
msgid "reboot (optional) - Reboot After Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2019
msgid ""
"Reboot after the installation is successfully completed. If you are "
"installing {PRODUCT} on IBM System{nbsp}z in command line mode (using xref:"
"sect-kickstart-commands-cmdline[cmdline (optional) - Perform Installation in "
"Command Line Mode]), this command is necessary for a fully automated "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2021
msgid ""
"For other completion methods, see the [command]#halt#, [command]#poweroff#, "
"and [command]#shutdown# Kickstart options."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2026
msgid ""
"Use of the [command]#reboot# command *may* result in an endless installation "
"loop, depending on the installation media and method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2029
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--eject#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2030
msgid ""
"Attempt to eject the installation media (if installing from a DVD) before "
"rebooting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2031
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--kexec#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2032
msgid ""
"Use this option to reboot into the new system using the `kexec` kernel "
"switching mechanism instead of a full reboot, bypassing the BIOS/Firmware "
"and boot loader."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2034
#, no-wrap
msgid "shutdown (optional) - Shut Down After Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2037
msgid "Shut down the system after the installation has successfully completed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2039
msgid ""
"For other completion methods, see the [command]#halt#, [command]#poweroff#, "
"and [command]#reboot# Kickstart options."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2041
#, no-wrap
msgid "%addon (optional) - Include an Anaconda Add-on"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2044
msgid ""
"You can expand the basic [application]*Anaconda* and Kickstart functionality "
"by using custom add-ons specified using the [command]#%addon# section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2046
msgid ""
"To use an add-on in your Kickstart file, add the [command]#%addon "
"_addon_name_ _options_pass:attributes[{blank}]# command. The section must be "
"closed with an [command]#%end# statement. For example, to use the "
"[application]*Kdump* add-on, which is included by default on some "
"installations, use the following block:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2049
#, no-wrap
msgid "%addon com_redhat_kdump --enable --reserve-mb=128%end\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2053
msgid ""
"The [command]#%addon# section does not have any options of its own; all "
"options depend on the add-on being used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2055
msgid ""
"For more information about [application]*Anaconda* add-ons, see the link:+"
"+https://vpodzime.fedorapeople.org/anaconda-addon-development-guide/+"
"+[Fedora Anaconda Addon Development Guide]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2057
#, no-wrap
msgid "%anaconda (optional) - Additional Anaconda Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2060
msgid ""
"This section, introduced in {PRODUCT} 22, is used to specify additional "
"configuration options for the installer. Commands inside this section only "
"control the behavior during installation, not on the installed system. The "
"only command currently available inside this section is xref:sect-kickstart-"
"commands-pwpolicy[pwpolicy (optional) - Change the Default Password Policy]. "
"The [command]#%anaconda# section must end with `%end`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2062
msgid ""
"In interactive installations (using the graphical or text interface), the `/"
"usr/share/anaconda/interactive-defaults.ks` file contains the default "
"[command]#%anaconda# section. To change the defaults, you must create a "
"`product.img` file with a Kickstart file replacing the default one, and pass "
"this file to [application]*Anaconda* using a boot option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2064
msgid ""
"When using a Kickstart file, you can override the default [command]#"
"%anaconda# section by using the section again in your custom Kickstart."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2066
#, no-wrap
msgid "%include (optional) - Include Contents of Another File"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2069
msgid ""
"Use the [command]#%include _/path/to/file_pass:attributes[{blank}]# command "
"to include the contents of another file in the Kickstart file as though the "
"contents were at the location of the [command]#%include# command in the "
"Kickstart file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2071
#, no-wrap
msgid "%ksappend (optional) - Append Contents of Another File"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2074
msgid ""
"The [command]#%ksappend _url_pass:attributes[{blank}]# directive is very "
"similar to xref:sect-kickstart-commands-include[%include (optional) - "
"Include Contents of Another File] in that it is used to include the contents "
"of additional files as though they were at the location of the [command]#"
"%ksappend# command. The difference is in when the two directives are "
"processed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2076
msgid ""
"[command]#%ksappend# is processed in an initial pass, before any other part "
"of the Kickstart file. Then, this expanded Kickstart file is passed to the "
"rest of [application]*Anaconda* where all [command]#%pre# scripts are "
"handled, and then finally the rest of the Kickstart file is processed in "
"order, which includes [command]#%include# directives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2078
msgid ""
"Therefore, [command]#%ksappend# provides a way to include a file containing "
"[command]#%pre# scripts, while [command]#%include# does not."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2080
#, no-wrap
msgid "%packages (required) - Package Selection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2083
msgid ""
"Use the [command]#%packages# command to begin a Kickstart section which "
"describes the software packages to be installed. This section must end with "
"an [command]#%end# statement."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2085
msgid ""
"You can specify packages by _environment_, _group_, or by their package "
"names. Several environments and groups that contain related packages are "
"defined. See the `repodata/comps.xml` file in your installation source for "
"environment and group definitions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2087
msgid ""
"The `comps.xml` file contains a structure describing available environments "
"(marked by the `<environment>` tag) and groups (the `<group>` tag). Each "
"entry has an ID, user visibility value, name, description, and package list. "
"If the group is selected for installation, the packages marked `mandatory` "
"in the package list are always installed, the packages marked `default` are "
"installed if they are not specifically excluded, and the packages marked "
"`optional` must be specifically included even when the group is selected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2089
msgid ""
"You can specify a package group or environment using either its ID (the "
"`<id>` tag) or name (the `<name>` tag)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2094
msgid ""
"To install a 32-bit package on a 64-bit system, you will need to append the "
"package name with the 32-bit architecture for which the package was built - "
"for example, [package]*glibc.i686*. The [option]#--multilib# option also "
"must be specified in the Kickstart file; see the available options below."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2101
msgid ""
"[application]*Initial Setup* does not run after a system is installed from a "
"Kickstart file unless a desktop environment and the [application]*X Window "
"System* were included in the installation and graphical login was enabled. "
"This means that by default, no users except for `root` will be created. You "
"can either create a user with the [option]#user# option in the Kickstart "
"file before installing additional systems from it (see xref:sect-kickstart-"
"commands-user[user (optional) - Create User Account] for details) or log "
"into the installed system with a virtual console as `root` and add users "
"with the [command]#useradd# command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2104
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifying Environments, Groups and Packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2106
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifying an Environment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2107
msgid ""
"In addition to groups, you specify an entire environment to be installed:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"%packages\n"
"@^Infrastructure Server\n"
"%end\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2117
msgid ""
"This command will install all packages which are part of the `Infrastracture "
"Server` environment. All available environments are described in the `comps."
"xml` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifying Groups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2119
msgid ""
"Specify groups, one entry to a line, starting with an `@` symbol, and then "
"the full group name or group id as given in the `comps.xml` file. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2128
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#%packages#\n"
"@X Window System\n"
"@Desktop\n"
"@Sound and Video\n"
"[command]#%end#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2132
msgid ""
"The `Core` and `Base` groups are always selected - it is not necessary to "
"specify them in the [command]#%packages# section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2134
msgid ""
"The `comps.xml` file also defines groups called `Conflicts (_variant_)` for "
"each variant of {PRODUCT}. This group contains all packages which are known "
"to cause file conflicts, and is intended to be excluded."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2135
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifying Individual Packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2136
msgid ""
"Specify individual packages by name, one entry to a line. You can use the "
"asterisk character (`*`) as a _wildcard_ in package names. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"%packages\n"
"sqlite\n"
"curl\n"
"aspell\n"
"docbook*\n"
"%end\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2149
msgid ""
"The `docbook*` entry includes the packages [package]*docbook-dtds*, "
"[package]*docbook-simple*, [package]*docbook-slides* and others that match "
"the pattern represented with the wildcard."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2150
#, no-wrap
msgid "Excluding Environments, Groups, or Packages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2151
msgid ""
"Use a leading dash (`-`) to specify packages or groups to exclude from the "
"installation. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2159
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"%packages\n"
"-@Graphical Internet\n"
"-autofs\n"
"-ipa*fonts\n"
"%end\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2166
msgid ""
"Installing all available packages using only `*` in a Kickstart file is not "
"supported, even if you exclude the `@Conflicts (_variant_)` group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2170
msgid ""
"You can change the default behavior of the [command]#%packages# section by "
"using several options. Some options work for the entire package selection, "
"others are used with only specific groups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2171
#, no-wrap
msgid "Common Package Selection Options"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2174
msgid ""
"The following options are available for the [command]#%packages#. To use an "
"option, append it to the start of the package selection section. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2178
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#%packages --multilib --ignoremissing#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2180
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nocore#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2181
msgid "Do not install the `@Core` group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2182
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--ignoremissing#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2183
msgid ""
"Ignore any packages, groups and environments missing in the installation "
"source, instead of halting the installation to ask if the installation "
"should be aborted or continued."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2184
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--excludedocs#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2185
msgid ""
"Do not install any documentation contained within packages. In most cases, "
"this will exclude any files normally installed in the `/usr/share/doc*` "
"directory, but the specific files to be excluded depend on individual "
"packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2186
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--multilib#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2187
msgid ""
"Configure the installed system for multilib packages (that is, to allow "
"installing 32-bit packages on a 64-bit system) and install packages "
"specified in this section as such."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2189
msgid ""
"Normally, on a 64-bit system, only packages for this architecture (marked as "
"`x86_64`) and packages for all architectures (marked as `noarch`) would be "
"installed. When you use this option, packages for 32-bit systems (marked as "
"`i686`) will be automatically installed as well, if available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2191
msgid ""
"This only applies to packages explicitly specified in the [command]#"
"%packages# section. Packages which are only being installed as dependencies "
"without being specified in the Kickstart file will only be installed in "
"architecture versions in which they are needed, even if they are available "
"for more architectures."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2192
#, no-wrap
msgid "Options for Specific Package Groups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2195
msgid ""
"The options in this list only apply to a single package group. Instead of "
"using them at the [command]#%packages# command in the Kickstart file, append "
"them to the group name. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2202
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#%packages#\n"
"@Graphical Internet --optional\n"
"[command]#%end#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2205
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nodefaults#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2206
msgid ""
"Only install the group's mandatory packages, not the default selections."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2207
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--optional#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2208
msgid ""
"Install packages marked as optional in the group definition in the `comps."
"xml` file, in addition to installing the default selections."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2210
msgid ""
"Note that some package groups, such as `Scientific Support`, do not have any "
"mandatory or default packages specified - only optional packages. In this "
"case the [option]#--optional# option must always be used, otherwise no "
"packages from this group will be installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2212
#, no-wrap
msgid "%pre (optional) - Pre-installation Script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2215
msgid ""
"You can add commands to run on the system immediately after the Kickstart "
"file has been parsed, but before the installation begins. This section must "
"be placed towards the end of the Kickstart file, after the actual Kickstart "
"commands, and must start with [command]#%pre# and end with [command]#%end#. "
"If your Kickstart file also includes a [command]#%post# section, the order "
"in which the [command]#%pre# and [command]#%post# sections are included does "
"not matter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2217
msgid ""
"You can access the network in the [command]#%pre# section. However, the "
"_name service_ has not been configured at this point, so only IP addresses "
"work, not URLs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2219
msgid ""
"The pre-installation script section of Kickstart *cannot* manage multiple "
"install trees or source media. This information must be included for each "
"created Kickstart file, as the pre-installation script occurs during the "
"second stage of the installation process."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2224
msgid ""
"Unlike the post-installation script, the pre-installation script is not run "
"in the `chroot` environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2228
msgid ""
"The following options can be used to change the behavior of pre-installation "
"scripts. To use an option, append it to the [command]#%pre# line at the "
"beginning of the script. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#%pre --interpreter=/usr/bin/python#\n"
"--- Python script omitted --\n"
"[command]#%end#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2238
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2276
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--interpreter=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2239
msgid ""
"Allows you to specify a different scripting language, such as Python. Any "
"scripting language available on the system can be used; in most cases, these "
"will be `/usr/bin/sh`, `/usr/bin/bash`, and `/usr/bin/python`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2240
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2298
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--erroronfail#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2241
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2299
msgid ""
"Display an error and halt the installation if the script fails. The error "
"message will direct you to where the cause of the failure is logged."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2242
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2300
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--log=#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2243
msgid "Logs the script's output into the specified log file. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2247
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#%pre --log=/mnt/sysimage/root/ks-pre.log#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2250
msgid ""
"For an example of a pre-installation script, see xref:sect-kickstart-example-"
"pre-script[Example Pre-installation Script]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2252
#, no-wrap
msgid "%post (optional) - Post-installation Script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2255
msgid ""
"You have the option of adding commands to run on the system once the "
"installation is complete, but before the system is rebooted for the first "
"time. This section must be placed towards the end of the Kickstart file, "
"after the actual Kickstart commands, and must start with [command]#%post# "
"and end with [command]#%end#. If your Kickstart file also includes a "
"[command]#%pre# section, the order of the [command]#%pre# and [command]#"
"%post# sections does not matter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2257
msgid ""
"This section is useful for functions such as installing additional software "
"or configuring an additional name server. The post-install script is run in "
"a chroot environment, therefore, performing tasks such as copying scripts or "
"RPM packages from the installation media do not work by default. You can "
"change this behavior using the [option]#--nochroot# option as described "
"below."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2262
msgid ""
"If you configured the network with static IP information, including a name "
"server, you can access the network and resolve IP addresses in the [command]#"
"%post# section. If you configured the network for `DHCP`, the `/etc/resolv."
"conf` file has not been completed when the installation executes the "
"[command]#%post# section. You can access the network, but you cannot resolve "
"IP addresses. Thus, if you are using `DHCP`, you must specify IP addresses "
"in the [command]#%post# section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2266
msgid ""
"The following options can be used to change the behavior of post-"
"installation scripts. To use an option, append it to the [command]#%post# "
"line at the beginning of the script. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2273
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#%post --interpreter=/usr/bin/python#\n"
"--- Python script omitted --\n"
"[command]#%end#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2277
msgid ""
"Allows you to specify a different scripting language, such as Python. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2281
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#%post --interpreter=/usr/bin/python#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2284
msgid ""
"Any scripting language available on the system can be used; in most cases, "
"these will be `/usr/bin/sh`, `/usr/bin/bash`, and `/usr/bin/python`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2285
#, no-wrap
msgid "[option]#--nochroot#"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2286
msgid ""
"Allows you to specify commands that you would like to run outside of the "
"chroot environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2288
msgid ""
"The following example copies the file `/etc/resolv.conf` to the file system "
"that was just installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2295
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[command]#%post --nochroot#\n"
"cp /etc/resolv.conf /mnt/sysimage/etc/resolv.conf\n"
"[command]#%end#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2301
msgid ""
"Logs the script's output into the specified log file. Note that the path of "
"the log file must take into account whether or not you use the [option]#--"
"nochroot# option. For example, without [option]#--nochroot#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2305
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#%post --log=/root/ks-post.log#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2308
msgid "with [option]#--nochroot#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2312
#, no-wrap
msgid "[command]#%post --nochroot --log=/mnt/sysimage/root/ks-post.log#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2315
msgid ""
"For an example of a post-installation script, see xref:sect-kickstart-"
"example-post-script[Example Post-installation Script]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2317
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example Kickstart Configurations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2320
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2324
#, no-wrap
msgid "Advanced Partitioning Example"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2323
msgid ""
"The following is an integrated example showing the [command]#clearpart#, "
"[command]#zerombr#, [command]#part#, [command]#raid#, [command]#volgroup#, "
"and [command]#logvol# Kickstart options in action:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2342
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"clearpart  --drives=hda,hdc\n"
"zerombr\n"
"# Raid 1 IDE config\n"
"part raid.11 --size 1000  --asprimary --ondrive=hda\n"
"part raid.12 --size 1000  --asprimary --ondrive=hda\n"
"part raid.13 --size 2000  --asprimary --ondrive=hda\n"
"part raid.14 --size 8000              --ondrive=hda\n"
"part raid.15 --size 16384 --grow      --ondrive=hda\n"
"part raid.21 --size 1000  --asprimary --ondrive=hdc\n"
"part raid.22 --size 1000  --asprimary --ondrive=hdc\n"
"part raid.23 --size 2000  --asprimary --ondrive=hdc\n"
"part raid.24 --size 8000              --ondrive=hdc\n"
"part raid.25 --size 16384 --grow      --ondrive=hdc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2349
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# You can add --spares=x\n"
"raid /     --fstype xfs  --device root  --level=RAID1 raid.11 raid.21\n"
"raid /safe --fstype xfs  --device safe  --level=RAID1 raid.12 raid.22\n"
"raid swap  --fstype swap --device swap  --level=RAID1 raid.13 raid.23\n"
"raid /usr  --fstype xfs  --device usr   --level=RAID1 raid.14 raid.24\n"
"raid pv.01 --fstype xfs  --device pv.01 --level=RAID1 raid.15 raid.25\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2355
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# LVM configuration so that we can resize /var and /usr/local later\n"
"volgroup sysvg pv.01\n"
"logvol /var           --vgname=sysvg --size=8000     --name=var\n"
"logvol /var/freespace --vgname=sysvg --size=8000     --name=freespacetouse\n"
"logvol /usr/local     --vgname=sysvg --size=1 --grow --name=usrlocal\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2361
msgid ""
"This advanced example implements LVM over RAID, as well as the ability to "
"resize various directories for future growth."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2363
msgid ""
"First, the [command]#clearpart# command is used on drives `hda` and `hdc` to "
"wipe them. The [command]#zerombr# command initializes unused partition "
"tables."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2365
msgid ""
"Then, the two drives are partitioned to prepare them for RAID configuration. "
"Each drive is divided into five partitions, and each drive is partitioned "
"into an identical layout."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2367
msgid ""
"The next part uses these pairs of physical partitions to create a software "
"RAID device with RAID1 level (mirroring). The first four RAID devices are "
"used for `/` (root), `/safe`, `swap` and `/usr`. The fifth, largest pair of "
"partitions is named `pv.01` and will be used in the following part as a "
"physical volume for LVM."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2369
msgid ""
"Finally, the last set of commands first creates a volume group named `sysvg` "
"on the `pv.01` physical volume. Then, three logical volumes (`/var`, `/var/"
"freespace` and `/usr/local`) are created and added to the `sysvg` volume "
"group. The `/var` and `/var/freespace` volumes have a set size of 8 GB, and "
"the `/usr/local` volume uses the [option]#--grow# option to fill all "
"remaining available space."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2374
msgid ""
"The above example uses identifiers `hda` and `hdc` to identify disk drives. "
"You should use unique identifiers, such as a disk labels or an UUIDs, to "
"identify disk drives. See the note in introduction to this appendix."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2378
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example Pre-installation Script"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2381
msgid "The following is an example [command]#%pre# section:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2383
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sample %pre Script"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2402
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"%pre\n"
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"hds=\"\"\n"
"mymedia=\"\"\n"
"for file in /proc/ide/h* do\n"
"mymedia=`cat $file/media`\n"
"if [ $mymedia == \"disk\" ] ; then\n"
"hds=\"$hds `basename $file`\"\n"
"fi\n"
"done\n"
"set $hds\n"
"numhd=`echo $#`\n"
"drive1=`echo $hds | cut -d' ' -f1`\n"
"drive2=`echo $hds | cut -d' ' -f2`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: pages/appendixes/Kickstart_Syntax_Reference.adoc:2422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#Write out partition scheme based on whether there are 1 or 2 hard drives\n"
"if [ $numhd == \"2\" ] ; then\n"
"#2 drives\n"
"echo \"#partitioning scheme generated in %pre for 2 drives\" > /tmp/part-include\n"
"echo \"clearpart --all\" >> /tmp/part-include\n"
"echo \"part /boot --fstype xfs --size 75 --ondisk hda\" >> /tmp/part-include\n"
